oakcurric:unit-2992
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Dance: traditional dances of the British Isles"@en ;
  curric:slug "dance-traditional-dances-of-the-british-isles" ;
  rdfs:comment """A stylistic approach develops Action-Space-Dynamics-Relationships to study dances
  from other times and places reviewing how and why motifs are repeated and developed.
  Pupils develop an understanding of the impact of accompaniment, landscape and other design
  features on action content."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils build on their prior learning of specific action content, alongside
  cross curricular links and cultural capital, progressing previous work on relationships.
  Clear movement language and stylistic features provide a framework from which pupils
  collaborate to create original dances, applying fundamental features of the selected style,
  developing their understanding of formations, motif development and stance. Pupils continue
  to respond to accompaniment. The content is typically energetic and so pupils develop stamina
  and strength alongside cooperation and team-work.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2992-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2992-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2992-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2992-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2992-5 ;
  curric:id "2992"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.998641Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-3018
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Athletics: athletic challenges refined"@en ;
  curric:slug "athletics-athletic-challenges-refined" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will challenge pupils to apply their knowledge and skills into a series
  of competitions. Pupils will experience competition across multiple areas of athletics and
  will have to work individually and collaborate together in teams to apply the correct
  techniques in order to be successful."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit of work, pupils will need to draw upon all of their prior
  learning of a vast range of athletic activities and strive to apply this understanding to the
  best of their ability through different competition formats. This unit will teach pupils
  about their body composition and enable pupils to develop an understanding of the events and
  activities they are suited to. Later, pupils will have the chance to work in teams where they
  will be challenged to select the events they should each compete in, specific to their own
  unique skill sets.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3018-9 ;
  curric:id "3018"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.004293Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-engagement-and-enjoyment .

oakcurric:unit-3014
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Striking and fielding games: striking and fielding tactics through rounders"@en ;
  curric:slug "striking-and-fielding-games-striking-and-fielding-tactics-through-rounders" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will challenge pupils to consistently apply effective tactics for both
  batting and fielding through rounders. Pupils will utilise their prior knowledge of
  batting and fielding tactics and consider when, where and why they will apply these during
  a game."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to develop pupils' understanding of batting and
  fielding and the skills and tactics required for both the batting and fielding teams. In this
  unit, pupils will be challenged to apply their learning through rounders and teach pupils how
  to use rounders specific skills when batting and fielding, to win a modified game. Later in
  the unit pupils will have to think carefully about creating and adapting tactics, making any
  necessary adaptations in order to ensure their team has the greatest chance of overcoming
  their opponent.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3014-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3014-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3014-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3014-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3014-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3014-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3014-7 ;
  curric:id "3014"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.114506Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-2988
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: maintaining possession and stopping an attack through basketball"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-maintaining-possession-and-stopping-an-attack-through-basketball" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ ability to apply the principles of attack vs
  defence through basketball. Pupils will develop their movement competence in passing,
  moving and dribbling and apply these skills to create shooting opportunities. When
  defending, pupils will learn how to stop an attack."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Previously, pupils developed their passing, dribbling and shooting skills,
  without the focus on a particular sport or activity. This essential prior learning is now
  completely transferable into this second invasion unit that looks closer at using skills such
  as passing, dribbling and shooting through basketball. Pupils will be able to take a closer
  look at some of the more basketball specific rules and techniques such as how to shoot and
  the rules governing dribbling.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2988-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2988-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2988-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2988-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2988-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2988-6 ;
  curric:id "2988"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.117030Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-2983
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: mindfulness and meditative balances"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-mindfulness-and-meditative-balances" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit will explore how we feel in our minds and in our bodies, when we
  experience various emotions. Pupils will learn how to execute meditative balances while
  focusing, to help combat feelings of anxiety. Pupils will gain an awareness of how to
  apply these techniques in day-to-day life."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have a strong understanding of the importance of
  exercise and how we can keep our bodies healthy. This unit introduces pupils to a more
  indepth look at the importance of having a healthy mind. Exploring meditative balances and
  relaxation techniques will introduce pupils to an entirely new concept that will help to
  support their mental wellbeing and overall fitness. The skills learnt in this unit, will
  support pupils to feel calmer and focused in all subsequent learning.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2983-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2983-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2983-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2983-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2983-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2983-6 ;
  curric:id "2983"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.119907Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-personal-and-emotional .

oakcurric:unit-2991
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Gymnastics: symmetry and asymmetry"@en ;
  curric:slug "gymnastics-symmetry-and-asymmetry" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will focus on exploring movements and balances in symmetrical and
  asymmetrical ways. Pupils will create and perform sequences that incorporate symmetrical
  and asymmetrical balances on apparatus, applying flow. Pupils will learn how to include
  canon and unison in their sequence creation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have already learnt how to design sequences on apparatus by
  including movements and balances with changes in level and direction. In this unit, pupils
  will be challenged to now think about more complex themes such as Symmetry and asymmetry,
  which add new layers of thinking to their pair and group work. Pupils will also be introduced
  to canon and unison and have to think creatively about the design of their sequences to
  utilise these key components to ensure their sequences are highly creative and aesthetically
  pleasing.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2991-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2991-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2991-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2991-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2991-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2991-6 ;
  curric:id "2991"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.122611Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-3016
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Dance: the power of unity"@en ;
  curric:slug "dance-the-power-of-unity" ;
  rdfs:comment """A narrative approach develops a wider range of creative responses to issue based
  work employing Action-Space-Dynamics-Relationships in a cohesive manner. Pupils express
  individuality through character-based work, reflecting on social issues. Pupils create
  dances using binary and ternary forms."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils continue to broach challenging and complex concepts that draw upon
  multiple, interconnected factors. This will deepen their understanding of issue-based work in
  dance and how this is used as a tool for advocacy and activism as introduced in the previous
  unit alongside developing and combining their physical, expressive, choreographic and
  analytical skills in preparation for key stage 3. This unit has potential to synthesise and
  draw upon all elements covered in previous units to enable pupils to unify their skills into
  a cohesive performance.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3016-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3016-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3016-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3016-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3016-5 ;
  curric:id "3016"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.125249Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-connect-cultural-and-ethical-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-3008
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Athletics: enhanced athletic challenges"@en ;
  curric:slug "athletics-enhanced-athletic-challenges" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will challenge pupils to consolidate their knowledge, understanding and
  ability to sprint effectively, individually and within a team. Pupils will show self
  motivation to improve their technique for throwing a shot put and explore and develop an
  understanding of how to hurdle safely."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already understand the difference between running for speed and
  distance. They can jump for distance and throw for distance using a Javelin. This unit
  introduces pupils to the hurdles, which is a more complex event, challenging running for
  speed in a unique way. Pupils will be able to draw on their prior learning of throwing far as
  they transfer their learning into throwing a shot put, which requires alterations to the
  previous techniques they have mastered. Throughout the unit, pupils will have the chance to
  apply their developing movement competence through competitions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3008-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3008-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3008-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3008-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3008-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3008-6 ;
  curric:id "3008"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.180282Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-personal-and-emotional .

oakcurric:unit-2987
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games:  maintaining possession and stopping an attack in ball games"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-maintaining-possession-and-stopping-an-attack-in-ball-games" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ ability to apply the principles of attack vs
  defence, focussing on how to use their passing, moving and dribbling skills to create
  shooting opportunities as well as defensive principles to stop an attack. Pupils will work
  together in teams to create simple tactics."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The unit will extend pupils’ understanding of invasion games, developing
  the principles of attack and defence. This invasion unit builds on prior learning by looking
  at the application of dribbling in attack, as well as defending as a team to stop the
  opposition’s attack. The focus will be through a ball skills lens as opposed to focusing on a
  specific sport to continue to enable the effective transfer of skills across multiple sports
  and activities. Later, pupils will have the opportunity to work together in teams to design
  tactics and strategies as they attempt to beat their opponents.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2987-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2987-2 ,
