    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3001-8 ;
  curric:id "3001"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.202696Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-2976
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Outdoor adventurous activities: team challenges"@en ;
  curric:slug "outdoor-adventurous-activities-team-challenges" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit of work will explore what makes an effective team through different
  problem-solving tasks and challenges. Throughout the unit, there will be a focus on pupils
  developing their communication skills, essential to working within a team to complete the
  challenges successfully."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Throughout KS1, pupils explored the idea of teamwork and began to develop
  and apply simple strategies to solve problems while developing their ability to collaborate
  in teams. This is the first unit that pupils will experience in KS2 and so it is essential
  that this unit prepares pupils for all future learning experiences that centre around working
  together in teams. Communication is an integral aspect of team work and so by focusing on
  this throughout the unit of work, pupils will gain the necessary undertaking of
  communication, to be able to use and apply this knowledge in all later units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2976-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2976-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2976-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2976-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2976-5 ;
  curric:id "2976"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.204606Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership .

oakcurric:unit-3010
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Outdoor adventurous activities: leadership"@en ;
  curric:slug "outdoor-adventurous-activities-leadership" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will enable pupils to identify the different attributes that make an
  effective leader and apply effective leadership skills to support and guide others. Pupils
  will learn to lead their team in different games and competitive challenges, supporting
  their team to apply effective tactics."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit of work explores the concept of leadership in more depth than
  previously. Pupils will be able to use all their learning around what makes an effective team
  covered in previous outdoor and adventurous activities units, to really delve deep into the
  important skill of leadership. Throughout the unit, pupils will then have the opportunity to
  really test their leadership skills and develop a strong understanding of the importance of
  effective leadership when applying effective tactics as strategies to complete team
  challenges.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3010-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3010-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3010-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3010-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3010-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3010-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3010-7 ;
  curric:id "3010"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.206525Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership .

oakcurric:unit-2994
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Athletics: athletic challenges developed"@en ;
  curric:slug "athletics-athletic-challenges-developed" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will challenge pupils’ integrity and resilience when developing their
  sprinting technique, analysing their own performance. Pupils will compare sprinting to
  running for distance and pacing. The unit will introduce throwing for distance with
  javelins and explore the basics of triple jump."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have developed a good understanding of running fast, jumping far
  and throwing far. In this unit, pupils will analyse their technique for sprinting and make
  decisions as to how to improve. For the first time, pupils will compare the difference
  between running for speed and running for distance, introducing the concept of pacing. Pupils
  will draw on their prior knowledge of jumping in combination and apply this understanding
  while learning about the triple jump. Later, pupils will have the opportunity to use their
  developing throwing skills and try throwing for distance using a javelin.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2994-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2994-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2994-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2994-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2994-5 ;
  curric:id "2994"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.208414Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-personal-and-emotional .

oakcurric:unit-2984
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Athletics: athletic challenges"@en ;
  curric:slug "athletics-athletic-challenges" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit of work will focus on how we can use our bodies to run as fast as
  possible, exploring the correct technique individually and within teams to improve
  performance. Pupils will also begin to evaluate how to jump as far as possible and compare
  throwing accurately with throwing for distance."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know how to run, jump, hop, skip and leap. Pupils will
  also have had the chance to apply these skills in games but also in simple athletic based
  competitions. This initial KS2 Athletics unit will be the first time that pupils start to
  explore these skills through a focused athletics lens. Pupils will be able to take their
  foundational understanding and expand this into a more detailed look at the specific
  techniques required in a range of athletic activities.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2984-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2984-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2984-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2984-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2984-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2984-6 ;
  curric:id "2984"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.279257Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-2980
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Striking and fielding games: fielding vs batting"@en ;
  curric:slug "striking-and-fielding-games-fielding-vs-batting" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit introduces batting vs fielding. Pupils will develop an understanding of
  the purpose of each team and learn how to apply a variety of skills such as throwing and
  stopping the ball to keep the batter’s score low as well as their competence in striking
  in order to score points when batting."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' understanding of using throwing, hitting and
  striking skills in order to win a game. By drawing on this prior knowledge and understanding
  from KS1, pupils will develop integrity as they take that first step in learning about
  striking and fielding games, developing their competence at executing a variety of skills.
  This initial unit will take a generic look at the batting and fielding before later starting
  to utilise these skills in more focused units later in KS2.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2980-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2980-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2980-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2980-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2980-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2980-6 ;
  curric:id "2980"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
