oakcurric:unit-2995
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Swimming: an introduction to core aquatic skills and survival swimming"@en ;
  curric:slug "swimming-an-introduction-to-core-aquatic-skills-and-survival-swimming" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit provides an introduction to core aquatic skills by teaching buoyancy,
  floating and moving through water on their fronts and backs, whilst increasing physical
  fitness in the water. It develops pupils' ability to rotate in the water and teaches them
  how to breathe whilst swimming."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This swimming unit is the second in a series of four swimming units and is
  the first pool-based unit. This unit starts to develop pupils' ability to move through the
  water, ensuring confidence is being built and familiarity with the swimming pool is
  developed. Having already learnt the basic knowledge on land for arm and leg actions, this
  unit introduces the movement in the water. It builds on their knowledge of healthy, active
  lifestyles in the previous unit and begins to prepare them for competitive swimming in the
  next, by developing both stroke technique and physical fitness.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2995-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2995-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2995-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2995-4 ;
  curric:id "2995"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.331242Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3015
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Gymnastics: matching and mirroring"@en ;
  curric:slug "gymnastics-matching-and-mirroring" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will enable pupils to explore what we mean by matching and mirroring
  movements. Pupils will be able to create sequences of movements with accuracy and fluidity
  using a range of apparatus. Pupils will effectively evaluate their sequences and find ways
  to improve and develop them further."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know how to create sequences that include a vast range of
  movement and balance ideas. This unit will teach pupils about matching and mirroring and
  challenge pupils to think carefully as to how they can create sequences with a partner that
  include matching and mirroring movements. This challenging theme requires careful selection
  of movements and multiple opportunities for accurate evaluation. Later, pupils will work in
  larger groups, to pull all of their creative skills together, to create a variety of
  different sequences that showcase a range of skills and creative components.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3015-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3015-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3015-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3015-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3015-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3015-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3015-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3015-8 ;
  curric:id "3015"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.367449Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection .

oakcurric:unit-2999
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: shooting, scoring and denying space through hockey"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-shooting-scoring-and-denying-space-through-hockey" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit will enable pupils to enhance their attacking and defensive skills
  through hockey. Pupils will learn the game specific skills, understanding when, where and
  why to apply these skills. Pupils will create effective tactics for attack and defence,
  applying them successfully in modified games."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Previously, pupils have looked at using and applying more complex
  attacking and defensive skills and tactics through a ball games unit, without the focus on a
  specific sport. This unit will serve to extend that challenge further by enabling pupils to
  showcase their understanding through hockey specifically. As well as applying the
  transferable skills and understanding required for invasion games, pupils will also be taught
  the game specific skills, rules and tactics that apply to the game of hockey.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2999-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2999-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2999-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2999-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2999-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2999-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2999-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2999-8 ;
  curric:id "2999"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.369716Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-2981
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Gymnastics: movements, balances and sequence composition"@en ;
  curric:slug "gymnastics-movements-balances-and-sequence-composition" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit of work introduces pupils to the idea of changes in levels and direction
  when creating and performing sequences in pairs and in groups. Pupils will reflect on the
  best way to create their sequences, combining both changes in level and direction, with
  balances and using a range of apparatus."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on the strong foundation pupils will already have
  creating gymnastic movements and balances. Pupils already know how to link movements with
  flow and can do so using a range of different movements and balances. This foundation is
  essential as pupils will be challenged to improve their creative skills as they design
  sequences on a variety of apparatus. Pupils will learn to include more advanced skills such
  as changes in level and direction, working in pairs and groups to evaluate and improve their
  performances.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2981-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2981-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2981-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2981-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2981-5 ;
  curric:id "2981"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.504622Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-2997
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Outdoor adventurous activities: orienteering"@en ;
  curric:slug "outdoor-adventurous-activities-orienteering" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ ability to orientate a map to locate points. Pupils
  will follow a set route and think strategically in order to reach as many points as
  possible in a set time. Pupils will develop their ability to collaborate with others and
  work as a team to complete the challenges."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already have a strong understanding of how we can work effectively
  as a team and why this is important. So far, pupils have focused on solving problems in
  teams, so this unit challenges pupils to apply this understanding through the uniquely
  different lens of orienteering. The unit develops pupils’ map reading skills alongside the
  development of communication and cooperation. Later, pupils have to apply their knowledge of
  orienteering and team work in competitive activities, where they will be challenged to think
  strategically, in order to be successful.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2997-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2997-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2997-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2997-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2997-5 ;
  curric:id "2997"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.507130Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership .

oakcurric:unit-3007
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: stamina, strength and flexibility"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-stamina-strength-and-flexibility" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will teach pupils the meaning of strength, flexibility and the
  cardiovascular elements of fitness. Pupils will perform cardio, flexibility and strength
  focused circuits developing their own fitness and enhance their understanding of the
  importance of healthy active lifestyles."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides pupils with the opportunity to take part in physical
  activities that build their understanding and knowledge of stamina, strength and flexibility.
  The unit will start to combine all prior learning around the importance of a healthy active
  lifestyle and inspire pupils to take ownership of their own health and wellbeing. Pupils will
  be challenged to further develop their own fitness and consider their levels of activity
  outside of their physical education lessons. Later in the unit pupils have the chance to
  perform personal best efforts to challenge their fitness.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3007-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3007-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3007-3 ,
