    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3007-7 ;
  curric:id "3007"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.527566Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3815
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Parkour: developing confidence and creative movement"@en ;
  curric:slug "parkour-developing-confidence-and-creative-movement" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will focus on introducing the fundamentals of parkour, learning how to
  move efficiently and creatively. Pupils will learn how to run, jump, land, balance and
  vault safely with a focus on good body control, coordination and spatial awareness."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have already learnt how to design creative sequences incorporating
  jumps and turns to create moments of flight. This unit will allow pupils more freedom and
  creativity to learn new skills. Pupils will develop their confidence, improving their problem
  solving skills as well as understanding the importance of safe risk-taking and learning to
  overcome challenges in a fun and supportive setting.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3815-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3815-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3815-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3815-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3815-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3815-6 ;
  curric:id "3815"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.529464Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 .

oakcurric:unit-2978
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: principles of attack and defence in netball"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-principles-of-attack-and-defence-in-netball" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit will introduce pupils to the principles of attack and defence, with a
  particular focus on passing, moving and scoring in netball. Pupils will learn how to keep
  possession and score in order to win a modified game. The unit will also focus on the
  basic rules of the game to aid understanding."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to develop pupils’ understanding of invasion games.
  Previously, pupils developed a basic understanding of the principles of attack and defence
  through generic ball games. This essential prior learning is fully transferable into this
  second invasion unit. Pupils will take a closer look at some of the more sport specific
  skills in netball, such as developing their motor competence in passing and moving and
  footwork. Later, pupils will also consider new strategies linked to the basic positions that
  they haven't explored in the generic unit.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2978-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2978-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2978-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2978-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2978-5 ;
  curric:id "2978"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.559726Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-3005
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Gymnastics: flight"@en ;
  curric:slug "gymnastics-flight" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will enable pupils to explore and perform a variety of jumps, knowing
  how to take off and land safely. Pupils will create sequences in groups, combining a
  variety of jumps and turns on apparatus with changes in level, direction, canon,unison and
  flow."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have already learnt how to think creatively about the design of
  their sequences to utilise canon and unison, with a focus on different gymnastics themes.
  This unit explores a unique aspect of gymnastics where we focus on flight and use jumps and
  turns to create moments of flight. This unit will allow pupils to use all their learning so
  far and really test their creativity as they construct their movement sequences and include
  flight in key moments of the sequence. Pupils will be ready to use their integrity, as they
  strive to create the best performance possible.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3005-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3005-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3005-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3005-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3005-5 ;
  curric:id "3005"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.561624Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-personal-and-emotional .

oakcurric:unit-2989
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Net and wall games: tactics to overcome an opponent through pickleball"@en ;
  curric:slug "net-and-wall-games-tactics-to-overcome-an-opponent-through-pickleball" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupil’s understanding of how to beat an opponent in net
  based games with a specific focus on pickleball. Pupils will enjoy learning how to create
  space to win points and develop their competence when using a paddle to pay forehand and
  backhand shots."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know why we have to aim at space using accurate throwing
  skills in order to beat an opponent. In this unit, pupils have the opportunity to expand on
  their understanding of net based games and begin some basic paddle work as they develop
  forehand and backhand techniques with increasing competence. Once pupils can control a ball
  with a paddle, they will explore the concept of creating space for the next shot, in order to
  beat their opponent.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2989-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2989-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2989-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2989-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2989-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2989-6 ;
  curric:id "2989"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.646081Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-engagement-and-enjoyment .

oakcurric:unit-2996
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Outdoor adventurous activities: solving problems"@en ;
  curric:slug "outdoor-adventurous-activities-solving-problems" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit of work will develop pupils’ ability to apply effective teamwork through
  different problem-solving challenges. Throughout the unit, there will be a focus on
  pupils' ability to apply skills essential to working within a team as well as creating and
  applying effective tactics together."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils continue to develop their understanding of effective team work in
  this unit on problem solving. The unit requires pupils to apply their knowledge of
  communication to solve a variety of problems in the most efficient way possible. The problems
  pupils are exposed to will significantly vary in design, to really test pupil’s developing
  understanding of creating and applying tactics as well as deepening their knowledge of what
  makes an effective team, enabling pupils to use this knowledge in the upcoming games units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2996-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2996-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2996-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2996-4 ;
  curric:id "2996"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.765361Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership .

oakcurric:unit-3017
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: stamina, strength and flexibility refined"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-stamina-strength-and-flexibility-refined" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit of work will consolidate pupils' understanding of strength, flexibility
  and the cardiovascular elements of fitness. Pupils will focus on enhancing their own
  fitness and understanding the importance of taking ownership of their own health and
  wellbeing in order to lead healthy active lives."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Previously, pupils will have the opportunity to take part in a variety of
  circuits, understanding what happens in their bodies, specific to different components of
  fitness. This unit will start to combine all prior learning around the importance of a
  healthy active lifestyle and inspire pupils to take ownership of their own health and
  wellbeing. Pupils will be challenged to further develop their own fitness and consider their
  levels of activity outside of their physical education lessons.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3017-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3017-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3017-3 ,
