oakcurric:unit-3013
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Net and wall games: tactics to overcome an opponent through badminton"@en ;
  curric:slug "net-and-wall-games-tactics-to-overcome-an-opponent-through-badminton" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will teach pupils to apply their understanding of how to create space to
  win a point through badminton. Pupils will refine their understanding of when to apply the
  forehand and backhand in a game situation and think tactically as to how to take control
  of the game from the serve."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already have a strong understanding of how to beat an opponent by
  creating space and using forehand, backhand and volley shots at the right time. In this unit,
  pupils have the opportunity to develop their knowledge of net based games further, as they
  develop and apply their understanding through badminton. Pupils’ competence in executing
  backhands, forehands, and volleys will be developed further through badminton and later in
  the unit, pupils will learn how to use the serve to take control of the game and increase the
  likelihood that they can overcome their opponent in games.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3013-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3013-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3013-3 ,
