oakcurric:unit-3009
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Swimming: strokes, distance and safe self rescue"@en ;
  curric:slug "swimming-strokes-distance-and-safe-self-rescue" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit will develop pupils' swimming competence so they can swim at least 25m.
  Pupils will start to apply a range of swimming strokes (front crawl, backstroke and
  breaststroke), learning how to motivate themselves and others. Pupils will learn to
  perform safe self-rescue in a range of situations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is the third in a series of four units and builds on the
  foundational understanding pupils have already achieved in swimming. This unit will take
  pupils from beginner swimmers, to more competent swimmers, as it develops their movement
  competence in more advanced strokes. This unit will prepare pupils for the final swimming
  unit, which will build upon and develop their safe rescue skills. Learning how to support and
  motivate others will enable pupils to improve their teamwork and communication in all areas
  of PE.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3009-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3009-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3009-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3009-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3009-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3009-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3009-7 ;
  curric:id "3009"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.005861Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-personal-and-emotional .

oakcurric:unit-3012
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: scenarios, tactics and power play through tag rugby"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-scenarios-tactics-and-power-play-through-tag-rugby" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will challenge pupils to consistently demonstrate their competence in
  applying attacking and defensive skills in a variety of game based scenarios through tag
  rugby. Pupils will create and apply tactics in games, adapting them as the game situation
  changes, in order to beat the opposition."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Previously, pupils have experienced adapting their tactics and strategies
  in a variety of game based scenarios, in the unit focused on ball games. This unit will teach
  pupils how to apply their understanding through tag rugby specifically. Pupils will apply the
  transferable skills and understanding required for invasion games and be taught the game
  specific skills, rules and tactics that apply to the game of tag rugby. Later in the unit,
  pupils will have the opportunity to apply tag rugby specific powers to take advantage of
  their opponents at the opportune moment in the games.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3012-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3012-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3012-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3012-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3012-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3012-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3012-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3012-8 ;
  curric:id "3012"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.044222Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-3003
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Gymnastics: counter balance and counter tension"@en ;
  curric:slug "gymnastics-counter-balance-and-counter-tension" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will focus on exploring counter balance and counter tension using the
  floor and apparatus. Pupils will learn how to perform a range of balances in pairs and
  compose sequences that consistently incorporate flow. Pupils will evaluate their sequences
  and reflect on how to make improvements."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit explores a new, more complex theme in which pupils have to work
  in pairs to create balances that rely on both partners using each other’s bodies to ensure
  the balance is safe and still. Once pupils have been able to create both counter balance and
  counter tension balances, they will utilise their prior learning of movement and flow,
  including flight, as they link the balances on a range of apparatus in pairs and in groups.
  Pupils will have to think strategically, to compose their sequences which will prepare pupils
  for their future gymnastics learning.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3003-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3003-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3003-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3003-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3003-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3003-6 ;
  curric:id "3003"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.077982Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection .

oakcurric:unit-2979
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Net and wall games: tactics and strategies to overcome an opponent"@en ;
  curric:slug "net-and-wall-games-tactics-and-strategies-to-overcome-an-opponent" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit of work will introduce pupils to the basic principles of attacking and
  defending in net based games. Pupils will explore where, when and why we throw the ball on
  a mini court, in order to win a game. Pupils will show resilience as they start to use
  rackets in order to control the ball."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to net based games by exploring beating an
  opponent on a mini court. In KS1, pupils will have already developed an understanding of how
  to use a racket or a bat to control a ball and send a ball accurately into space and so this
  unit takes that next step into the basic application of these skills. Beginning the unit by
  using their hands, pupils will aim at space and try to use their accurate throwing skills in
  order to beat an opponent. Later, pupils will have the opportunity to progress onto using a
  racket or bat and show resilience as they develop their technique.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2979-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2979-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2979-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2979-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2979-5 ;
  curric:id "2979"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.091594Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-personal-and-emotional .

oakcurric:unit-3011
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: scenarios, tactics and power play in ball games"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-scenarios-tactics-and-power-play-in-ball-games" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit of work will challenge pupils to consistently develop effective
  attacking and defensive skills and be able to apply these in a variety of game based
  scenarios. Pupils will create and apply tactics in games, adapting them as the game
  situation changes, in order to beat the opposition."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know how to create and apply effective attacking and
  defensive tactics in games. This unit serves to expose pupils to a variety of game based
  scenarios in order to teach pupils how to adapt their tactics and strategies according to the
  situation in the game. Later, pupils will also have the chance to explore the idea of
  selecting and applying ‘super powers’ to give their team a strategic advantage and the
  opportune moment in a game. The use of powers will really enhance pupils’ creative thinking
  and further challenge their ability to make effective decisions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3011-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3011-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3011-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3011-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3011-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3011-6 ;
  curric:id "3011"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.110876Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking .

oakcurric:unit-2998
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: shooting, scoring and denying space in ball games"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-shooting-scoring-and-denying-space-in-ball-games" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit will challenge pupils to enhance their attacking and defensive skills.
  Pupils will have a clear understanding of when, where and why to apply these skills during
  a game. Pupils will be able to develop effective tactics for both attacking and defending
  and apply these successfully in games."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know how to apply attacking skills such as passing and
  moving, dribbling and shooting as well as basic defensive skills in order to stop attacks.
  This unit will pull this prior learning together and challenge pupils to start to create and
  apply effective attacking and defensive tactics in a variety of ball games. Pupils will be
  further challenged to understand more complex defensive strategies such as how to deny space,
  in order to stop an attack in later units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2998-9 ;
  curric:id "2998"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.256761Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking .

