oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22400-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: focusing on yourself and continuing to try hard to improve your technique
  demonstrates self-motivation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22400-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: treating our opponents with respect when we race against one another
  develops cooperation and trust"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.399940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22457-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: mime sequences combined with meditative balances require movements and
  stillness to portray different emotions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401695Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22457-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: to improve our mime and meditative balance sequences, the actions must
  flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401699Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22457-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: it is helpful to be able to link the emotions expressed in our mimes to the
  relevant meditative balance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401703Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22457-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: to manage our emotions throughout the day, we can use meditative balances to
  focus and calm our bodies and minds."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401707Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22457-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: we should strive to help others in the group who find meditative balances
  and relaxation techniques difficult."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401711Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22379-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: performing in groups to peers requires accurate timings, fluidity and quality
  movements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401737Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22379-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: knowing that sequences must be performed with control and extension is
  essential to effective evaluation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22379-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: evaluating other group's work, requires understanding changes in level and
  direction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401745Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22379-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: accurately evaluating another group's work requires demonstrating a
  responsibility to improve their performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401748Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22379-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: trusting the evaluation made by our peers to improve our performance is
  essential to developing sequences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22461-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: when running longer distances we need relaxed shoulders, arms swinging
  naturally and a comfortable stride length."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22461-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: long distance running requires a steady pace and rhythm that you can keep up
  for a long time saving energy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401763Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22461-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: if we sprint during a long distance race and do not pace ourselves, we run
  out of energy and have to slow down."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401767Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22461-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: pacing ourselves over a longer distance requires us to be self-disciplined to
  make sure we can finish the race."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401771Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22461-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: we can help our partners improve their pacing by communicating whether they
  need to speed up or slow down."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.401774Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22596-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: high quality sequences require consistent flow, accurate timing and high
  quality movements from start to finish."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22596-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: designing a group sequence on apparatus requires careful planning, which
  shows flow and accurate timing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402480Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22596-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: deciding which movements to perform as a group requires analysing a variety
  of options."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402484Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22596-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: communicating feedback to our group members with respect will help the
  development of the sequence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402488Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22596-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: showing determination to improve our sequence demonstrates self-motivation to
  strive for our best performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22351-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: a chest pass requires pushing the ball with both hands, step into the pass and
  follow through extending arms."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402498Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22351-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: when receiving the ball, track it with your eyes as the ball leaves your
  teammates hands getting your hands ready."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402502Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22351-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: to keep possession of the ball, it is important to pass and receive
  accurately in space away from defenders."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22351-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: even when we make a mistake, being determined to improve our chest passing
  inspires others and shows integrity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402513Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22351-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: it is important to respect our partners and work together to improve our
  throwing accuracy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402517Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22576-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: we must pass and move accurately and consistently with good technique in order
  to create attacking opportunities."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402521Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22576-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: executing effective overlaps and dummy passes increases the chances of scoring
  in a game."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402525Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22576-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: making effective decisions as to which tactics to use in a game can increase
  our chances of success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402531Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22576-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: striving to improve our performance by identifying our strengths and
  weaknesses demonstrates strong integrity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402535Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22576-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: suggesting ways our team can improve their performance shows excellent
  leadership and resourcefulness."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402539Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22488-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: creating a successful shooting chance requires us to dribble, pass and move
  accurately and consistently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402544Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22488-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: preventing an attack requires a quick transition into defensive positions to
  deny the opposition space and time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402548Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22488-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: adapting tactics as the situation in the game changes requires problem
  solving and increases chances for success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402551Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22488-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: never giving up even when our team is losing; striving to succeed instead
  demonstrates great self discipline"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402555Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22488-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: listening to our team, explaining tactics when someone doesn't understand,
  shows effective communication."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.402559Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

