# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Misconceptions
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:misconception-problem-solving-something-done-best
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Problem solving is something done best in teams."@en ;
  curric:correction "Problem solving independently can develop a great ability to strategise."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086122Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-better-roll-ball-game-boccia
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "It is always better to roll the ball in the game of Boccia."@en ;
  curric:correction """Sometimes it is useful to throw the ball to knock an opponent's ball out of
  the way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086217Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-throwing-underarm-step-forward-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When throwing underarm, you step forward with the same foot to
  throwing arm."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When throwing underarm, you should step forward with your opposite foot to
  throwing arm."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086597Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-canon-means-different
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think canon means doing different actions."@en ;
  curric:correction """Canon involves doing the same actions but starting at different times to the
  other person/people."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086706Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-need-go-run-go-gym
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You need to go for a run or go to the gym to develop your aerobic fitness."@en ;
  curric:correction """You can improve your aerobic fitness wherever you are, with little to no
  equipment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-copy-actions-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think they should copy the actions on the same side as the leader."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to perfom the actions on the opposite side to the leader as if
  they are performing in a mirror."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-youre-either-flexible-person-youre
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You're either a flexible person or you're not."@en ;
  curric:correction """Everyone can improve their range of movement with a commitment to some
  stretching and flexibility training."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087159Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-balance-something-need-gymnastics
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Balance is something you just need in gymnastics."@en ;
  curric:correction """Balance is needed in many everyday activities and across many different
  sports."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087393Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-strength-training-done-gym-fitness
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Strength training can only be done in a gym or fitness suite."@en ;
  curric:correction """Strength training can easily be completed at home with different
  resources."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087414Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-golf-higher-score-get-better
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "In golf, the higher the score you get, the better the result."@en ;
  curric:correction """In golf, it is better to score a lower score by rolling the ball into a hole
  in as few shots as possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087428Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-its-best-aim-ball-towards
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "It's best to aim the ball towards the other player."@en ;
  curric:correction """To try and beat the other player and score points, it is useful to aim into
  the space so your opponent has less chance of sending it back."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-catch-ball-without-letting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils catch the ball without letting it bounce near the back of the court
  when the ball would have gone out."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In these games, the ball has to bounce to get pupils used to moving out the
  way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087545Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dens-built-inside
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Dens can only be built inside."@en ;
  curric:correction """Den's can be built anywhere. They are a great way to connect with nature if
  built outside."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-same-action-full
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think they have to do the same action for the full 8 beats."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils can select different actions, 1 per beat if they wish, and they don't
  have to be the same actions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088197Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-need-equipment-specific-gym-space
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You need equipment and specific gym space to complete circuits."@en ;
  curric:correction """You can complete circuits anywhere using alternative activities and
  equipment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088654Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-need-go-fast-possible-complete
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You need to go as fast as possible to complete an obstacle course."@en ;
  curric:correction """Problem solving and taking your time to strategise is what leads to the
  successful completion of an obstacle course."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088660Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-playing-game-focus
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When playing a game, you should only focus on what you are doing."@en ;
  curric:correction """When playing a game, sometimes it is better to also focus on what your
  opponent is doing so you can use tactics to beat them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089176Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-jumping-requires-use-our-legs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Jumping just requires the use of our legs."@en ;
  curric:correction "To be able to jump far, you must use your legs and arms together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089210Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-starting-position-describes-shape-make
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A starting position only describes the shape you make."@en ;
  curric:correction """A starting position involves both the shape you make, as well as the
  location. It refers to both what you do and where you do it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093673Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dance-one-motif
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A dance only has one motif."@en ;
  curric:correction """Most dances will contain several motifs, these can be as short and simple as
  a gesture or more complex sequences. If they are performed more than once in a dance, then
  they are a motif."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-successful-hit-target
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think they are only successful if they hit a target."@en ;
  curric:correction """Celebrate pupils for using the correct technique and for trying hard and
  provide demonstrations to support learning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093694Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hit-their-shots-hard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils hit their shots too hard and the ball travels out of court. Pupils do
  not return to the ready position after every shot. Pupils struggle to rally when the ball
  can only bounce once."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to follow through on their swing to develop more control
  over the shot. Remind pupils to return to the middle and be in the ready position after
  every shot. Allow pupils to continue to rally even when the ball bounces twice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093720Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bowling-pupils-prioritise-throwing-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When bowling, pupils prioritise throwing the ball with as much force as
  possible."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that applying force to their bowls is beneficial,
  but good accuracy is essential to ensure 'no balls' aren't thrown. Pupils should focus on
  developing excellent accuracy before attempting to apply more force."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093731Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cold-water-shock-occurs-winter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Cold water shock only occurs in the winter."@en ;
  curric:correction "Cold water shock can occur all year round in waters around the UK."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093745Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-climbing-using-steps
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that climbing out using the steps is the quickest and safest way
  to exit the pool in an emergency."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Climbing out over the side of the pool is often quicker and most appropriate
  when there is a whole class of students and prevents waiting or queueing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094077Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-dance-formations-involve
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that all dance formations involve facing forwards, side
  by side."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In traditional dances, the performers typically look straight ahead, but the
  formations may involve people being side by side, one behind the other, in a circle or
  sometimes something different such as a star, a square or a double circle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-triple-jump-pupils-collapse-middle
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """In the triple jump, pupils collapse the middle 'step phase' rather than
  getting equal height and distance from every phase."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand the importance of all phases of the jump, especially
  the step phase and that they understand all phases of the triple jump should contribute to
  an equal proportion of distance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-running-around-bases-stopped
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils are running around the bases and they have stopped on a base, they
  often lose concentration or do not understand when they need to run again, which can
  result in a run out."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that even though they have stopped, they still need
  to focus in order to make it round the bases without getting out. The batter can continue
  running again once the bowler has bowled the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094595Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mark-same-pupil-leaving
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils mark the same pupil, leaving attackers open in space. Pupils swarm
  around and only mark the player with the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to communicate and ensure everyone is responsible for a
  different player. Remind pupils of the rule concerning marking. This rule is in place to
  enable the pupil in possession to look up and make effective passing decisions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094603Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-defending-game-situation-pupils-tend
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When defending in a game situation, pupils tend to follow the ball which
  closes up the space and leaves other players unmarked."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that they need to stay close to the player they are marking and
  be prepared to intercept the ball when it is passed to their opponent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094615Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mistake-dribbling-fast-dribbling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often mistake dribbling fast and dribbling with control, which causes
  them to lose control of the ball. Often pupils won't catch the ball but just move straight
  into a dribble."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that dribbling fast is good but dribbling with control is
  essential. The better control they have, the faster they will be able to dribble. Remind
  them that they should receive the ball and assess the best option before dribbling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094632Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-once-pupils-start-link-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Once pupils start to link their mediative balances, they focus on creating a
  sequence of movements rather than the relaxation purposes of the process."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that medatitive balances aren't the same as gymnastic balances and
  provide examples to support pupil understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094640Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-tend-stick-simple-movements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils tend to stick with simple movements such as walking to move into
  balances and to link the sequence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that although we can walk, there are so many movement options and
  walking isn't the most exciting to watch. Encourage pupils to try a range of movement
  ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-making-contact-use-your-hands
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When making contact you always use your hands"@en ;
  curric:correction """Making contact can involve different body parts, e.g. foot to foot, elbow to
  shoulder, back to back. Using more unusual connections can make a dance appear more
  interesting to the audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094662Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-focus-winning-become-disappointed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils only focus on winning and become disappointed if they don't win."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to be motivated to try and win, but to understand that
  performing to the best of their ability and enjoying themselves is what they need to aim
  for."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095192Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-receiving-baton-turn-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils are receiving the baton, they turn their body to face the incoming
  runner to give them a better view and try to grab the baton from them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that although this technique may seem easier, it will cause
  their team to lose speed. Pupils should face forwards, with their hand out behind them and
  communicate to ensure the exchange is successful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-two-speeds-fast-slow
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "There are only two speeds, fast and slow."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are many speeds. Think of a race, everyone will be travelling as fast
  as they can but the winner will have been moving faster than the rest. Fast and slow guide
  us towards the rate at which we should move and may need more clarification."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095225Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-give-their-team-winning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils give up if their team is not winning."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that the more self-motvation, determination and collaboration
  they show, the more likely they are to succeed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095231Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-kick-quickly-possible
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that they should kick as quickly as possible, without using a
  glide between each breaststroke leg kick."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Breaststroke is most effective when there is a short glide in the streamlined
  position between each leg kick."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095250Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-breathe-little-breathe
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that they should breathe as little as often, or always breathe to
  the same side."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Breathing every 3 arms pulls maintains body position and oxygen supply to the
  working muscles."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095258Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bowling-pupils-focus-solely-bowling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When bowling, pupils focus solely on bowling powerfully and quickly every
  bowl, often causing them to bowl inaccurately or without proper technique."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that the accuracy of their bowling is crucial and
  that varying the speed and power of the bowls can actually make it trickier for the batter
  to hit the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-implemented-tactics-successful
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils believe that all implemented tactics will always be successful."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that tactics don't always work and they may need to
  react quickly to adapt them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095496Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-space-makes-activity
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that more space always makes an activity better or more
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In reality, too much space can make games too easy or boring because pupils
  don’t have to use skills like dodging, teamwork or quick thinking to avoid others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095501Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-frustrated-arent-winning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils get frustrated if they aren't winning. Pupils panic and rush decisions
  around passing and shooting, focusing more on the competition."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Award points for pupils and teams that show respect and apply determination
  throughout. Encourage pupils to take their time and consider the options before passing or
  shooting so they don't lose possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095507Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-shouldnt-start-feel
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that they shouldn't start to feel fatigued if they are pacing
  themselves and slow down or stop if they do."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils understand that it is normal to feel fatigued during the
  run, even when they are pacing themselves, and they need to push through this using
  determination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095513Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-follow-their-throw-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils follow through on their throw, they use excessive force which
  causes them to lose balance, impacting the throw and often causing them to step over the
  throwing line."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand the consequences of stepping over the throwing line
  - foul throw."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096108Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-using-props-like
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often assume that using props like handkerchiefs or scarves simply
  means waving them in the air."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If using props such as handkerchiefs or ribbons in dance these can exaggerate
  the actions and add flow to the action. Whereas props such as sticks or swords can also
  add sound. Props often help to communicate the theme or origin of a dance too."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096125Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-take-their-time
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget to take their time to pass and move and instead panic, rushing
  their passes and shooting far from the target."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to have patience to support each other to pass and move towards
  the target, and shoot when in a suitable position."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096130Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-move-throw-strike
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find when they move to throw/strike the ball, it goes somewhere
  different to where they had intended."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage the striker/thrower to turn their body, as well as their head and
  shoulders towards the space they would like the ball to go."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096143Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-hold-your-breath-hold-your
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You must hold your breath and hold your nose when your face is in the
  water."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Perfrom trickle breathing; gentle continuous bubbles when the face is in the
  water."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096766Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-make-pass-score
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will try and make a pass to score from too far away. Pupils run into
  the endzone boxes to receive a pass too early and are just standing still in the box."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to be closer to the scoring zones before trying to make a
  pass to score. Explain that if we just stand in the box, we aren't helping our team with a
  passing option."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096772Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-once-moved-space
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that once they have moved into a space, they can stay still and
  wait for the ball to come to them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils must be reminded to keep moving, creating angles for passes to the
  sides of their opposition. If they stand still, it makes it really easy for the defender
  to mark them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096781Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-balance-imaginary-stick
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget to balance the imaginary stick in their pairs and create
  movements that wouldn't work if they were using a real stick. Pupils also lose their focus
  during the movements and rush them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide lots of examples to support pupils to create movements while
  balancing an imaginary stick. Remind pupils of the importance of focus, control and slow
  deep breathing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096786Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-linear-formation-means-make-line
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Being in a linear formation means make a line one behind the other."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst this is an example of a linear formation, it could also involve the
  pupils being side by side or in a diagonal line. Linear formations can also meet or
  intercept to make patterns such as a 'V' or 'X' formation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096806Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-dip-wrong-time-dipping
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils dip at the wrong time, dipping too early, which has a negative impact
  on their running speed. Often pupils just dip their head forwards, rather than their upper
  body."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give pupils opportunities to practise implementing the dip, aiming for around
  3 steps before the finish line. Ensure pupils understand that a sprint race is measured
  when a runners upper body, shoulders cross the line, not their head."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096811Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-replicating-newtons-cradle
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that when replicating Newtons Cradle, when we make contact with
  others, we have to bump or push them away."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The actions don’t have to be bumps or pushes when making contact with a
  partner, but instead could be any action such as a lean, a step, a jump etc."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-pupil-leads-their-timing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """One pupil always leads so that their timing is out. Variations in angles of
  movement make the mirroring look uneven. Pupils move in the wrong direction so they are
  parallel instead of mirroring"""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should practise counting or using music to help them improve their
  timing. Pupils need to practise so they have identical body positions and use feedback to
  help improve this. Practise mirrored movements over and over to create muscle memory."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-game-main-role
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that in a game the main role is to attack and score,
  forgetting about their defensive duties and stopping the opponents."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight the value of both attacking and defending and encourage teams to
  work together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097223Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-adapting-task-everyone
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe when adapting a task that everyone needs the same level of
  challenge."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that everyone has different levels of skill,
  experience and confidence, therefore adapting a task should look to meet the needs of all
  the pupils engaging in it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097575Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-complicate-balances-holding-fail
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils over complicate the balances they are holding and fail to hold them
  still. This also means they will not be able to focus as they try to hold the balance."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to create a stable base, enabling their body to focus
  throughout and successfully use the balances as a tool to relax."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097581Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-triple-jump-consists
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often think the triple jump consists of a step, step and jump, rather
  than a hop, step and jump."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Allow pupils time to practise hopping and stepping and highlight the
  difference between the two. Pupils must understand that a hop requires them to land on the
  same foot they took off on, and a step is from one foot to the other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098373Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-pulse-rhythm-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that pulse and rhythm are the same thing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that pulse is the steady, consistent beat that runs through the music
  and rhythm is the pattern of sounds."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-successful-sequences-long
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may think that successful sequences are long and consist of lots
  of different movements and balances."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Successful sequences can be performed with control and flow. They can be
  short and may repeat some movements if the pupils feel this is the best decision to
  improve the quality of their performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098390Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-working-pairs-one-pupil-naturally
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When working in pairs, one pupil who is naturally faster moves ahead quickly
  from point to point, leaving their partner behind."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Both partners need to stay together so they can support each other with
  navigation and decision-making. If one person moves ahead alone, they miss the chance to
  communicate, plan effectively and succeed as a team."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098399Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-long-barrier-fielding
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils use the long barrier fielding technique, they do not join their
  heel with their knee therefore leaving a gap for the ball to roll through."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand the concept of creating a barrier and that they need
  to ensure they leave no gaps for the ball to roll through if they miss it with their
  hands."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098411Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-heart-symbolises-love
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A heart only symbolises love."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst love is the most common interpretation of a heart symbol, it can also
  represent unity, gratitude, hope, care, comfort, friendship, romance, resisting oppression
  and acceptance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098740Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-communicate-spray-paint-rush-around
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "To communicate spray paint we rush around the room, making hissing noises."@en ;
  curric:correction """To communicate the idea of using spray paint we need to perform smooth and
  flowing actions using control, balance and coordination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098746Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pretending-object-drama-dance
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pretending to be an object is drama, not dance."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pretending to be an object is often categorised as 'physical theatre'. This
  is where dance and drama overlap and it draws upon skills from both disciplines. A similar
  connection is made when dancers represent characters or scenes from a story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098765Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-creating-motif-represent-ideas-painting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When creating a motif to represent ideas from a painting, you must use the
  same action over and over again."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When creating a motif, you can demonstrate an action then repeat it by
  changing the size, level, direction, speed, force, using a different body part, adding an
  extra action, reversing the action or coordinating another action at the same time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098773Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-jump-high-possible-attempting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils jump as high as possible when attempting to clear a hurdle which can
  slow them down and negatively effect their rhythm."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to focus on their technique to help them jump the hurdles
  efficiently with a flat technique."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098799Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-your-fitness-fixed-cannot-changed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Your fitness is fixed and cannot be changed."@en ;
  curric:correction """Fitness can improve slowly and over time. Measuring our fitness only tells us
  what we can do on that day."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098808Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-initiate-turn-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget to initiate the turn with their head and don't spot their
  landing, which leads to disorientation and a lack of control."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should focus on looking where they want to land. You should start the
  spin with your eyes and your head."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-batting-pupils-focus-solely-hitting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When batting, pupils focus solely on hitting the ball with power, ignoring the
  positioning of the fielders."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that having awareness of fielders positions willl help them
  to aim and strike the ball into space. A powerful strike is not as effective if it goes
  towards a fielder."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-incorrect-hand-placement-performing-vaults
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Incorrect hand placement when performing vaults can lead to poor balance and
  coordination."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils perform with the correct hand position, using one hand for
  the lazy vault and opposite hand to foot with the step vault. Perform the vaults slowly to
  build confidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099170Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-comes-creating-sequence-pupils-include
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When it comes to creating a sequence, pupils include too many actions and the
  sequence is hard to follow as it goes on for a long time without following the rules of
  the structure."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise the importance of planning the sequence and use the worksheets to
  support with this. The sequence should only include the actions stipulated and should
  therefore follow a clear structure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099187Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-trying-move-another-person-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Trying to move another person means you do so as forcefully as you can."@en ;
  curric:correction """By starting gently, a person is able to judge the amount of effort that is
  likely be be required to attempt to move a solid object such as a sculpture made of stone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099218Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-telling-story-dance-narrative-dance
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Telling a story in dance (narrative dance) should include talking."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst some dances include dialogue, in dance a story is usually communicated
  solely through actions and the performers are usually silent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-batting-run-around-bases
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils are batting and they run around the bases, they often run inside
  the bases, which is against the rules of the game."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils know the rule that they must run around the outside of the
  bases when running."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099381Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-competition-pupils-tend-forget-learnt
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As it is a competition, pupils tend to forget what they have learnt and rush
  decisions around passing and shooting. Pupils get frustrated if not winning."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils have up to 4 seconds, so encourage them to take their time when making
  decisions. Award bonus points for pupils playing with integrity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099429Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-performance-perfect-improvements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may think that a performance should be perfect and if any
  improvements are suggested, they have failed or made a mistake."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Striving to be perfect is different to striving to do our best. It is good to
  want to perform at a high standard and it feels great when we achieve it, however, if we
  are seeking perfection, we might forget to celebrate everything we have achieved."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-move-wrong-direction-parallel
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils move in the wrong direction so they are parallel instead of mirroring.
  When pupils perform their sequence on apparatus, they lose control, extension and flow."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Practise mirrored movements to create muscle memory. Pupils should adapt
  their sequences to work on apparatus so they don't lose quality. Pupils can also focus on
  communication to help improve the quality of their sequence on apparatus."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099446Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-contribute-reflections-group-lack
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not contribute to reflections as a group as they may lack
  confidence to speak up in front of others. Pupils may lose flow in their sequence when
  they add balances."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage every pupil to contribute in group reflection tasks and consider
  ways in which everyone can give feedback. Pupils should think carefully about how they
  will get into and out of their balances to maintain flow throughout the sequence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099451Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dancing-duet-stay-same-partner
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When dancing a duet, you should always stay with the same partner."@en ;
  curric:correction """Quite often, if dancing a duet, we stay with the same partner, but in some
  social dances we change who we dance with as part of the dance. This helps a community get
  to meet new people."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-transition-aburptly-lower-body
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils transition aburptly from a lower body position leaning forwards to
  running upright, which causes them to slow down and lose their rhythm."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to transition smoothly as they accelerate towards top speed
  as doing this too quickly can cause a loss of speed. Allow opportunities for pupils to
  practise this and address the misconception when observed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101092Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-skip-travel-forwards
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When you skip, you always travel forwards."@en ;
  curric:correction """Skipping often involves travelling forwards, but it can also be performed on
  the spot or even travelling backwards."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101098Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-order-bring-graffiti
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that in order to bring graffiti 'tags' to life through movement,
  you have to write in the air."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Creating a 'tag' using your body can involve writing in the air, but it could
  also include making and holding a shape, or even using the colour, style or shading as the
  stimulus for your actions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101117Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-different-relaxation-techniques
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils rush different relaxation techniques and actions with their bodies when
  performing sequences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that mimicking different emotions requires
  concentration and controlled movements, which are often performed slowly in order calm our
  bodies."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101135Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-choose-throw-overarm-distance
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will choose to throw overarm from a distance even if this compromises
  accuracy."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Accuracy of an overarm throw takes time and practise. Pupils should try
  exploring both throwing techniques from different distances to judge what is their
  conformable throwing range."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101142Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-posture-doesnt-matter-hip-hop
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Posture doesn't matter in Hip hop dance."@en ;
  curric:correction """Posture immediately communicates clues about a dance style, whether it is
  forceful and energetic like Hip Hop or light and graceful like Ballet. It enables the
  audience to know what to expect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102083Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-hitting-ball-channel
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that hitting the ball into the channel is all they have to do
  to score a point, and they stay still after their shot."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils aim for channels to create space to try win the overall point and
  hitting the channel doesn't instantly result in a point being scored. After each shot,
  pupils should try to return to the ready position."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102089Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-leadership-means-boss
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that leadership means being the boss and that they should be
  the only ones with ideas."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Leadership is about guiding and supporting others, not dominating. True
  leaders listen, include others, and delegate responsibilities."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102094Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-effective-forms-communication
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils believe that all effective forms of communication are verbal."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that there are many different ways they can
  communicate through both verbal and non-verbal communication."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-wear-nose
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that you need to wear a nose clip to prevent water from going up
  your nose when swimming or rotating in the water."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Blowing out when performing rolls in the water stops water from going up your
  nose."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102115Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-signalling-help-water-done-waving
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Signalling for help in the water should be done by waving the arms about."@en ;
  curric:correction """Waving the arms in an emergency could be confusing. Signal for help by
  raising one arm directly upwards and shouting help."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102432Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-slow-throw-backstop-1st
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils are often too slow to throw from backstop to 1st base when trying to
  run the batter out, resulting in the batter being able to continue running around the
  bases."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When backstop has the ball, they need to react quickly and focus on a flat,
  hard throw to 1st base to try and run the batter out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102768Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-need-use-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils believe that they only need to use their arms when shooting."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that shooting effectively involves the whole body,
  paticularly the legs that give us more power. Coordinated body movement will be more
  successful than just arm strength."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102776Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rely-copying-others-get
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils rely on copying others to get the steps right rather than learning the
  steps themselves."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Exaplain to pupils the importance of showing resilience and rehearsing to
  become more familiar with the actions, directions and patterns."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103526Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-suggest-rolling-cartwheeling-turn
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils might suggest that rolling or cartwheeling is a turn to change
  direction."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Although a body rotates during a roll or cartwheel, it moves along one
  course, facing the same direction at the start and finish. This lesson focusses on
  changing the course that we are moving along which is achieved through turns and spins."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103565Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-switching-cooperative-rally
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle when switching from a cooperative rally to a competitive
  rally. Pupils may struggle to use their backhand and rely too much on their forehand."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A cooperative rally involves pupils trying to help one another to play longer
  rallies. A competitive game involves hitting the ball into space away from their opponent.
  Encourage pupils to use their forehand and backhand in rallies."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-become-fixated-specific-movements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils become too fixated on specific movements in their obstacle courses and
  become upset when others make adaptations."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Stress the importance of movement for enjoyment,and that adaptations are
  sometimes necessary so everyone can succeed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103576Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-generate-throwing-action-using
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils generate a throwing action using the the arm only."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to use all the body, rather than just the arm when throwing,
  to help generate power and balance when throwing over a greater distance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103861Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-stand-making-letter-shapes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils can only stand when making letter shapes."@en ;
  curric:correction "Pupils can lie, sit, or stand to make letter shapes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103873Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-continue-create-symmetrical-balances
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils continue to create symmetrical balances, confusing symmetry with
  asymmetry."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Provide models and continue to highlight the differenece between the two."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104827Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-humans-need-strong
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils might think that humans only need strong muscles if they want to
  excel in sports such as weight lifting and climbing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Strong muscles are essential for humans to complete everyday tasks including
  breathing, blinking, sitting, lifting, chewing etc. Strong muscles also help our joints to
  work effectively which helps to avoid injury and pain."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-tend-chase-ball-gravitate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils tend to chase after the ball and they all gravitate towards it as
  opposed to the player they are marking."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus on staying close to your opponent, wait for the pass to come to them
  and then attempt to intercept it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104922Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-throw-shuttlecock-correct
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to throw the shuttlecock into the correct position for
  their partner to hit a forehand. Pupils may struggle to hit the shuttlecock to the back of
  the court."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils may need to feed the shuttlecock overarm to get enough power behind
  their throw to feed to their partners forehand. Place the non-racket foot forward and
  follow through after hitting the shuttlecock to allow for more power behind the shot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-without-planning-logical
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils rush off without planning a logical route, leading to wasted time or
  missed checkpoints."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils allow time to plan their route with their partner and that they
  understand the value in doing this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105003Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-create-pathway-drawing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think they can create a pathway by drawing the letter shapes in the
  air."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Drawing letter shapes in the air produces 'air pathways'. This lesson is
  focusing on 'floor pathways' which require the pupils to travel along the shapes of the
  different letters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105212Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-demonstrate-changing-levels-stay-spot
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "To demonstrate changing levels, you have to stay on the spot."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst you may wish to remain on the spot, changing levels can be
  incorporated into other actions such as travelling or with other spacial elements such as
  pathways or directions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105240Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-jump-high-enough
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle to jump high enough to turn due to a weak push off. Pupils are
  wobbly and unbalanced when turning. Pupils turn too much or too little."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise bending the knees and pushing through the balls of the feet. Pupils
  should practise engaging their core muscles to help them turn with control. Make sure
  pupils focus on rotating from the shoulders and hips not just the arms."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105248Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-everyone-feel-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think everyone will feel the same way when they hear a piece of music
  and respond with the same actions and expressions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that we might feel and respond the same way, but it is just
  as likely that we will feel differently as a number of factors will influence how we feel,
  including our mood and experiences that day."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105259Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-mark-leaving-attackers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget who to mark, leaving some attackers unmarked and free to pass
  and move."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to work as a team to agree who they are marking so they can apply
  pressure effectively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-avoid-hitting-backhand-find
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils avoid hitting a backhand if they find it too difficult which disrupts
  their balance and positioning. Pupils may face the net rather than rotating their body
  when hitting the shuttlecock."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend time focusing on just the backhand shot to develop pupils' confidence
  so they will use the shot in a rally. Remind pupils to shift from the ready position, to
  then rotate their body to hit the shuttlecock so they can generate more power."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105271Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-effective-communication-involves
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that effective communication only involves speaking clearly to
  someone."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that communication works two ways. Speaking clearly
  is important, however listening attentively is equally important to ensure the information
  is received."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105277Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-place-their-foot-low
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often place their foot too low on the wall which affects their ability
  absorb and redirect impact. Pupils sometimes jump straight at the wall."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should aim to plant their foot around knee/waist height and remind
  pupils to push off the wall, not into it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105291Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-look-directly-their-feet
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often look directly down at their feet which shifts their head forward
  and throws them off their centre of gravity. Pupils are often overly tense when balancing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """For safety in parkour, pupils should focus just in front/ahead of their feet.
  Pupils should stay relaxed especially in their arms and shoulders."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105301Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-many-pupils-think-fall-water
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Many pupils think that if you fall in to water you should start swimming as
  quickly as possible."""@en ;
  curric:correction """But we need to teach them that if you fall into water, you should float on
  your back to regain your breath and calm yourself down, before assessing the situation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106108Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-importance-clear-instructions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget the importance of clear instructions and get side tracked in
  just wanting to win or complete the task."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that using a calm voice and giving clear instructions will
  develop better trust and confidence in a partner, ultimately leading to success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106129Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-stand-behind-defenders-waiting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils stand behind defenders when waiting to receive the ball. Pupils keep
  moving into space but don't look at the player with the ball to acknowledge they are ready
  to receive a pass."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to move to the side of the defender creating an angle for
  the pass. Support pupils to communicate (verbal and non verbal) when they are ready in a
  space."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106136Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-consider-performing-their-balances
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may only consider performing their balances on top of the
  apparatus."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Apparatus can be used in variety of ways to support pupils' weight; balances
  can be performed on top, against or under apparatus, e.g. feet on the apparatus with hand
  on the floor or feet on the floor with back against the apparatus."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106148Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-flexibility-challenged-holding-specific-postion
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Flexibility can only be challenged when we are holding a specific postion and
  staying still."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Flexibility of our muscles can be performed when still (static) and on the
  move (dynamic)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107096Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-teams-successful-score
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that teams are only successful if they score the most points or
  win against their opposition."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Scoring the most points or goals is one way you can measure success.
  Including all team members, playing fairly and improving are all equally important ways of
  being successful when competing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107505Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-reading-face-map-pupils-misidentify
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When reading the face map, pupils misidentify the equipment, especially when
  differentiating between quoits and cones."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to use the key when looking at their map, rather than just
  looking at the objects on the face. This will help them to identify what each object
  represents."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107511Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-harder-throw-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often believe that the harder they throw the ball, the better the pass
  will be."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise the importance of accuracy and remind the pupils that a softer,
  better-placed pass will be more effective and easier for teammates to receive."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107543Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-mime-refers-illustrating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that mime only refers to illustrating physical objects, e.g. a
  plate or a glass of water etc., and don't consider how mime can represent emotional
  responses too."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that mime is a powerful tool we can use to help us to
  understand and manage our emotions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107635Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-pupil-leads-other-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """One pupil always leads the other. Only one pupil can perform the movement with
  quality."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use strategies such as counting or music to help pupils move at the same
  time. Encourage pupils to ensure that both of them can perform the skills, and if they
  can't, they should work on improving or changing the movement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107649Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-line-symmetry-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget the line of symmetry in their balances. Pupils always mirror
  their partner when creating symmetrical balances and always want to connect to their
  partner using the same body parts."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The content in cycle 3 will help with this but pupils will need lots of model
  examples to see how symmetrical balances can still be created without always mirroring
  their partner."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108597Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recieve-ball-automatically-try
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils recieve the ball and automatically try to shoot, regardless of their
  position on the pitch/court."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that their shots will not be successful if they don't give
  careful consideration to the position they are in before shooting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108636Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-switch-hands-ball-hit
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may switch hands if the ball is hit towards their backhand side rather
  than using two hands on the racket to hit the ball. Pupils may place their dominant hand
  at the top of the racket handle."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should keep their dominant hand at the bottom of the racket handle for
  control and place their non dominant hand at the top to play a backhand shot with both
  hands on the grip. Explain that the hand at the bottom provides the control."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108642Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-aim-strike-ball-lot
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils aim to strike the ball with a lot of power which can lead to missed
  timed strikes and no contact being made."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Power can range from the small amount of power needed to make contact, to a
  lot of power to make the ball travel further."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108709Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-swimming-fast-important
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that swimming fast is most important."@en ;
  curric:correction """Slow, steady and energy efficient swimming is best for longer distance
  swimming."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108745Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-create-1-balance-idea
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils create 1 balance idea and think they are finished, instead of trying a
  range of ideas. Pupils only work on one part of the apparatus and fail to try a range of
  apparatus to create their ideas."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that they must try out multiple ideas and use a range of
  apparatus in order to be successful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109063Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-co-ordinate-letting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to co-ordinate, letting the ball bounce before serving
  underarm. Pupils struggle to aim diagonally across the court into the service box."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make sure pupils are bouncing the ball in front and to the side of their body
  and that they are stood side on to help them make contact with the serve. Pupils need to
  make sure their feet are lined up correctly to help them aim diagonally."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109070Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-bend-their-bowling-arm
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils bend their bowling arm and use an overarm throwing motion when
  releasing the ball, rather than using the correct cricket bowling action."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils are using a straight arm and proper follow through when
  bowling. Pupils should focus on becoming confident with this technique before attempting
  to apply more speed and power."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109078Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-generate-their-hitting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils try to generate their hitting power using just their arm, which results
  in them over swinging and missing the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that swining smoothly and keeping their eye on the ball is
  important. Pupils should bend their knees slightly and use their hips to rotate and
  generate power."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-moving-your-arms-faster-makes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Moving your arms faster makes you swim faster."@en ;
  curric:correction """When learning front crawl and backstroke pupils must have opportunity to
  catch the water and feel the water so that they are able to pull as much water as
  possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-implement-special-power
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that when they implement a special power, they will always be
  successful."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight the importance of good passing and moving skills when pupils use
  their special power, to increase chances of success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110067Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-become-fitter-work
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "To become fitter you must ‘work out’."@en ;
  curric:correction """Fitness can develop in many different forms. Whenever you are challenging
  your body physically, this will help you to become fitter."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-powerful-actions-performed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that powerful actions should be performed quickly."@en ;
  curric:correction """Powerful actions can be performed at any speed. However, rushing and moving
  too quickly can make it difficult to control the actions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110080Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-travelling-sideways-performed-side-step
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Travelling sideways can only be performed by a side step."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are many different ways to travel sideways, e.g. shuffling, stretching,
  wriggling, jumping."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111241Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-perform-canon-perform-same-action
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When you perform a canon, you have to perform the same action as each
  other."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst this is often true, the actions can vary, e.g., pupils may jump apart
  one at a time, yet each pupil may perform a different jump, or pupils may change shape. It
  is the staggered timing that is the essential element."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111266Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-balance-due-weak
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with balance due to weak core muscles. Pupils may always
  want to use the same apparatus in the same area."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Add some core strengthening exercises into the warm up and emphasise the
  importance of core strength in all activities. Encourage pupils to use a range of
  apparatus throughout the lesson to develop their confidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111272Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupil-loses-their-balance-struggle
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """If a pupil loses their balance, they may struggle to stand back up. Often,
  they instinctively put their hands on the pool floor, which can make it even harder to
  return to a standing position."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils move their knees under their chest, lift their head and pull back with
  their hands. They can pratise adapted burpees to get used to this movement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111898Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-throw-shuttlecock-net
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to throw the shuttlecock over the net. Pupils often grip
  the racket too tightly which can reduce power and control. Pupils often stand still after
  throwing/hitting the shuttlecock."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils use a beanbag instead of a shuttlecock. Lower the net/use cones.
  Emphasise relaxed hands for better control when gripping the racket. Returning to the
  ready position after every shot helps pupils develop their footwork and movement skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-travel-fast-without
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may try to travel too fast without having control of the ball on the
  racket. Pupils may want to hit the ball over the net instead of playing 'Floor tennis'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to move slowly to develop their hand eye coordination when
  using a racket before increasing their speed. Explain to pupils that floor tennis will
  help to develop better control when using the racket before they move on to hitting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-many-pupils-believe-harder-hit
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Many pupils believe that the harder they hit the ball, the better their shot
  will be. This leads to a lack of accuracy and technique."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to focus on using the correct technique and highlight the
  importance of accuracy over power."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111942Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-pass-ball-forward
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think they can pass the ball forward. Pupils get confused with the
  meaning of passing the ball backwards and think that means passing over their head, rather
  then in relation to their attack."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils of the rule that passes must go laterally or backwards, so the
  player receiving must not go ahead of the player in possession of the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111947Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-stand-still-once-space
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils stand still once they are in a space and just wait for the ball to come
  to them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that we must keep moving to find spaces to ensure our team always has
  several passing options. If we stand still, the defenders could intercept the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111967Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-bend-their-knees
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget to bend their knees on landing. Pupils bring their head to their
  knees when performing a tuck jump. Pupils forget to use their arms when jumping."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should repeatedly practise bending knees on landing. Pupils should
  raise their knees towards the chest in a tuck jump. Pupils should be reminded to swing
  their arms to give them momentum and to use their arms in the various jumps."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111978Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-stamping-something-frustrated-its-dance
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Stamping is something we do when we are frustrated; it's not a dance
  action."""@en ;
  curric:correction """All actions can be used in dance. Stamping could be used to communicate
  frustration or could be used to add emphasis, make rhythmic sounds or show strength."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-their-arm-strength
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils just use their arm strength to throw the shot, not realising the
  importance of using their legs to generate power."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils are crouching down into their back leg and pushing off strongly
  to create power when releasing the shot. Remind pupils that shot put is a push, not a
  throw."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-swimming-best-action
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that swimming is the best action in an emergency situation."@en ;
  curric:correction """Floating, treading water and heat retaining positions are often the best
  action in an emergency situation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112821Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-take-their-eyes-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils take their eyes off of the ball when they approach it, as they look to
  see where they are going to throw it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When pupils take their eyes off the ball, they increase the chances of
  misfielding it. Ensure pupils track the ball into their hands, before looking up to decide
  where to throw it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112827Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-discussing-their-tactics
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils rush when discussing their tactics as they just want to play the game.
  Not all pupils get to contribute to the team discussions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Praise and celebrate teams who discuss their tactics thoroughly, ensuring
  everyone contributes and that everyone understands."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112839Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-add-elements-their-sequences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As pupils add more and more elements to their sequences, the quality of their
  performance decreases. There may be issues with group dynamics as pupils work in bigger
  group sizes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Stress the importance of only moving on to add another element to the
  sequence once all members of the group are ready to move on. Pupils may have to delegate a
  leader or be encouraged to listen to each other when working in bigger groups."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112869Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-supported-someone-dont-anything
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When being supported by someone you don't have to do anything."@en ;
  curric:correction """It helps the 'supporter' if the 'supported' person is still, but they need to
  remain alert and actively hold their body firm, which makes it much easier for the
  'supporter' to absorb their weight and return them to an upright position."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-building-jump-pupil-steps-forward
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When building up to the jump, the pupil steps forward slightly, jumping off 1
  foot."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that jumping off 1 foot or stepping forwards before jumping
  is a foul. They must jump and land using both feet."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-skillful-gymnasts-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may think that having the most skillful gymnasts in their group
  will make it easier to create a group sequence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Creating sequences in groups needs lots of different skills which are just as
  important as physical skills. Groups will need to make thoughtful decisions, will need to
  rehearse responsibly and will need to work cooperatively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113065Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-keeping-accurate-timings
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils find keeping accurate timings hard and struggle to see how to adapt the
  sequence to improve this and make this easier."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to slow down their movements and to include simpler
  movements that both pupils in the pair can perform with confidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113148Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-completing-course-speed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that completing the course with speed is more important than
  completing it accurately."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight the importance of balancing speed with careful thinking and
  teamwork, to ensure pupils complete the course correctly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113164Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-emphasis-dance-means-making-actions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Emphasis in dance only means making actions bigger or more forceful."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasis is adding stress or importance and can involve making actions
  bigger/more forceful or smaller/less forceful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113738Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-insist-including-movements-balances
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils insist on including the movements and balances that they want to
  perform as part of the sequence, even if some members of the group cannot perform these
  correctly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Groups need to agree on the movements and balances that they are including in
  the sequence and ensure everyone is able to perform them correctly and safely."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113744Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-throw-much-force-aiming
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils throw with too much force when aiming for a target."@en ;
  curric:correction """Managing the right amount force of a throw requires practise and trial and
  error to judge how much force is needed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113755Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-perform-font-paddle
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that you have to perform a font paddle arm action as quickly as
  you can."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A long and steady pull is more energy efficient and can increase
  propulsion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113991Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-fielding-need-think
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that when fielding, they only need to think about how they use
  their hands when attempting to catch or stop a moving ball, which can cause them to miss
  the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand the importance of moving their feet quickly to
  ensure they are able to position their body behind the ball. This will increase their
  chances of stopping the ball from going any further."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114002Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-throw-ball-without
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may rush to throw the ball without checking where their opponent is
  positioned. Pupils may forgt to return to the ready position in the middle of the court on
  the baseline."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to scan the court and look for spaces away from their
  opponent. Remind pupils to return to the middle of the court on the baseline after every
  shot and adopt the ready position."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114010Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-curved-side-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils use the curved side of their stick."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to use the flat side of their stick, rotating it when
  changing direction. Challenge pupils, but be lenient as they develop this difficult skill."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114021Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-uncomfortable-vulnerable-reflecting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel uncomfortable or vulnerable when reflecting on the abstract
  ideas of the poem, which can make it difficult for them to focus, relax and link their
  work to the meaning of the poem."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Support pupils to open their minds to new concepts and to focus only on
  themself when reflecting. Explain to pupils that only by trying something with full effort
  and concentration can the benefits be felt."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114027Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-communicate-working-bigger
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle to communicate when working in bigger groups. Poor timing in
  unison and canon may result in a lack of flow throughout the sequence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should communicate and listen to each other's ideas. Pupils should
  develop ways to help them improve their timing, ensuring there are no long pauses when
  performing in unison and canon so their sequence still flows throughout."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114033Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-need-look-floor-avoid-swords
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You need to look at the floor to avoid the swords."@en ;
  curric:correction """If working carefully, it is possible to remember where the 'sword' markings
  are and avoid them. This skill takes a great deal of practice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114039Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-contrast-opposites
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Contrast has to be opposites."@en ;
  curric:correction """Opposites are an excellent example of a contrast since they are completely
  different. However, there are others, e.g. to contrast 'up' you could use 'forwards' since
  it is a distinctly different direction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114045Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-correct-interpretation-action-image
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "There can only be one correct interpretation of an action or image."@en ;
  curric:correction """Interpreting meaning of a symbolic action can vary depending on your previous
  experience and opinions, so people may view it differently and draw various conclusions.
  The important thing is to be able to justify your interpretation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114987Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-jump-balanced-take
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may rush the jump and not be balanced before they take off from the
  apparatus. Pupils may misplace their feet on the apparatus. Pupils may land with stiff
  knees or poor body position."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Always check balance and engage the core before jumping. Ensure a solid
  stance before jumping. Pupils should bend their knees to absorb impact on landing and make
  sure their weight is centered over their feet."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115104Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-travelling-around-circle-try-catch
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When travelling around in the circle you should try to catch up with the duet
  ahead of you."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When travelling around in the circle you should aim to maintain the same
  distance from the duets in front and behind you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115767Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-artists-think-ideas-whatever-artform
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Artists just think of ideas, whatever artform they work in."@en ;
  curric:correction """All artists, whether dancers, painters, actors or musicians, look to other
  artforms and the wider world for inspiration. Charlie Parker (musician) inspired Basquiat
  (painter) who later inspired Jay Z (musician)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115776Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-heart-muscle-because
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may not recognise the heart as a muscle because we cannot
  consciously move it in the same way we can other muscles in the body."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The body has voluntary and involuntary muscles. The heart is an involuntary
  muscle that doesn't require conscious thought to make it contract and send blood around
  the body. Exercising regularly can improve the strength and endurance of our heart."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115782Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-freely-move-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often think they can freely move their pivot foot by dragging and
  sliding it. Pupils continue to move a few steps when holding the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Reinforce the importance of keeping the pivot foot stationary and continue to
  practise the correct way to pivot. Remind pupils that stepping when holding the ball is a
  rule break and their team loses possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115787Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-take-flat-footed-leaning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often take-off flat footed or leaning backwards and look down during
  their jumps."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should take-off from the balls of the feet with knees and hips
  engaged, swinging their arms for more momentum. Pupils should ensure they keep their eyes
  locked on the landing spot from take-off to landing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115793Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-communicate-idea-show
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that to communicate an idea we have to show a picture."@en ;
  curric:correction "We can communicate ideas through our dance actions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116406Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-deflated-lack-self-motivation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils are deflated and lack self-motivation if their team does not have
  possession of the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Get pupils to think carefully about the tactics and strategies that can be
  used to prevent the attack from scoring and help the defensive team regain possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116412Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-defending-marking-pupils-focus-much
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When defending and marking, pupils focus too much on the ball instead of
  watching their opponent."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to always be aware of the player they are marking by
  constantly checking where they are. Discourage pupils chasing after the ball when their
  teamate is closer to it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116492Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-asking-pupils-hit-ball-pace
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When asking the pupils to hit the ball at pace, they may lose accuracy and
  control. You may have a wide range of abilities in your group which means that many of the
  games might not be competitive."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If pupils hit the ball too hard, remind them that accuracy and control is
  more important. Use the previous lessons to assess the ability of pupils so you can
  organise pairs who will have competitive games against one another."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116509Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-conversation-involves-speaking
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that a conversation only involves speaking aloud."@en ;
  curric:correction """In dance, we can show a conversation by using our actions to represent the
  words being spoken. We can communicate the idea of dialogue without saying a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117495Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-communicate-floating-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that to communicate 'floating' they must use jumps."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst jumping can communicate the sense of lift we associate with a balloon,
  the light, floating appearance comes from moving using a light, gentle dynamic which
  requires balance, control and coordination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117523Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-partner-ends-bearing-weight
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """One partner ends up bearing more weight than the other, leading to
  instability. Pupils may try complex counter balances before they have mastered the
  foundational skills."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show examples of counter balances where pupils are evenly distributing their
  weight. Make sure pupils can perform basic counter balances with quality before they
  attempt more complex balances."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117535Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-breaststroke-swam-head
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Breaststroke is always swam with the head up."@en ;
  curric:correction """Breaststroke can be swam with the head up in a survival situation or with the
  head submerging and lifting during each arm cycle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117560Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-working-partner-face-them
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "If working with a partner, you should always face them."@en ;
  curric:correction """It can be helpful to face the people you are working with when you are
  deciding upon the actions you will perform. However, once you have created the action
  content, you can use different formations and arrangements to make the work more
  interesting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117992Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dynamics-involve-either-speed-force
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Dynamics involve either speed or force, not both."@en ;
  curric:correction """Dynamics are a combination of both speed and force. We naturally use them
  both in every action we do, in dance we can use them to clearly communicate our dance
  idea, sometimes this requires greater emphasis on one or the other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118000Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-dribble-pass-effectively
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think they can only dribble or pass and not effectively combine both,
  struggling to transition between the 2 actions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus on the importance of both skills and how key decision making on when to
  use each action is vital."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118029Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-adding-players-making
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that adding more players and making the task bigger, makes it
  better and more enjoyable."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Too many players can mean some stand around and don’t get get chance to join
  in properly. Ensure the number of players, attackers and defenders is suitable for the
  task."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118038Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dynamics-mean-fast-slow-perform
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Dynamics mean how fast or slow you perform an action."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils think that dynamics only means how fast or slow you perform an action
  and forget that it is also about the force we apply."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-focus-tempo-music-matching
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils focus on the tempo of the music, matching the beat and tempo, instead
  of considering the full effect of the music in creating an emotional response. (e.g.,
  pupils run to fast music.)"""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that it is important to be still and listen to the music
  before moving. Pupils should also be reminded to consider their facial expression, ensuing
  this matches their movement responses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118763Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-underestimate-many-learnt-skills
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often underestimate many of the learnt skills and believe that shooting
  from anywhere on the court is effective."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils the importance of passing and dribbling into space, teamwork
  and positioning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-frustrated-lose-possession
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils get frustrated when they lose possession and fail to carry out their
  defensive tactics."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils how important it is to defend and try and stop the attack. If
  we give up, it's likely our opponents will score."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118788Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-avoid-hitting-backhand-shots
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils avoid hitting backhand shots. Pupils forget to return to the ready
  position. Pupils hit their forehands and backhands square on to the net."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Allow pupils time developing their backhand technique so they can use both
  shots in a rally. Remind pupils to return to the ready position after every shot. Pupils
  should have one foot slightly in front of the other so they in a side on position."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118805Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-tensing-their-body
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often believe that tensing their body (hands, face, arms, legs), will
  help them generate more speed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that this can actually slow them down, by affecting their
  running form and using energy inefficiently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119332Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-concentrate-freezing-still
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle to concentrate when they are freezing still or when they are
  deep breathing so the relaxation technique is ineffective."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to be reminded that the techniques only work if they focus and
  are still, concentrating on their breathing / the stillness."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119346Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-talking-loudly-shouting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe talking loudly or shouting is how they should communicate as a
  leader."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that shouting instructions isn’t the same as giving clear,
  helpful directions. As well as this, good communication works both ways and leaders should
  allow their teammates opportunities to speak too."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119358Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-longer-sequence-better
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that the longer the sequence is, the better it must be."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to understand that quality actions over quantity are essential
  when creating a sequence. Pupils should also be reminded to follow the sequence
  pattern/rules."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-emergency-situations-people-swim-without
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """In emergency situations people often swim without assessing the situation
  first."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Floating for 60 seconds in a star float and then treading water to identify
  the most appropriate action is best for assessing a survival situation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120355Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hit-ball-hard-batting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often hit the ball too hard when batting, not considering batting
  accuracy. Pupils hit the ball in the same space every time they bat which, if righthanded,
  is usually towards 2nd and 3rd base."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should focus on accuracy and control rather than power. Encourage
  pupils to change the angle of their bodies, front foot and backswing to help them hit the
  ball in different directions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120368Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-shout-teammates-make-mistake
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils shout at teammates when they make a mistake, causing teammates to be
  unmotivated and upset."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils of the importance of positivity and motivation, using kind and
  encouraging words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-swing-their-racket-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often swing their racket at the ball generating too much power when
  hitting a volley. Pupils hit the volley with their feet square to the net rather than side
  on."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The volley technique involves blocking the ball rather than swinging the
  racket back to hit the volley. Pupils should step into the volley so their bodies turn to
  the side when they hit a volley."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120483Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-stand-their-paddle-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often stand with their paddle down by their side and are not in the
  ready position. Pupils often wait for the ball to reach them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Keep repeating the ready positon throghout he lesson. Make sure pupils
  understand that the ball should only bounce once so they have to run to meet the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-leader-same-boss
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may think that being a leader is the same as being 'the boss' who
  tells everyone what to do and has all the ideas that others must follow."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Being a leader can involve making suggestions and sharing ideas. They might
  follow your way of thinking and come up with new ideas themselves. It can also involve
  asking other people for their opinions and listening carefully."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120495Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-balancing-easy-because
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some children may think that balancing is easy because it's just about staying
  still."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Balance requires strength and concentration to keep muscles under control in
  different positions. Balances should be held for at least 4 seconds and sometimes you need
  to make adjustments to maintain a balance. Holding a balance requires total focus."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120504Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-disregard-their-tactics-once
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils disregard their tactics once they start playing the game, getting
  distracted by everything else that is going on in the game."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand their tactics and make an effort to use them during
  the game. Highlight and praise pupils that manage this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122706Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-shout-instructions-attempt-make
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils shout instructions in an attempt to make themselves understood."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that using a calm voice will develop better trust and
  confidence in a partner."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122718Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-perform-their-sequence-apparatus
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils perform their sequence on apparatus, they lose control, extension
  and flow."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make sure that pupils carefully consider how they can adapt their sequences
  to work on apparatus so they don't lose quality. Pupils can also focus on communication to
  help improve the quality of their sequence on apparatus."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122723Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hold-relay-baton-hold
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils hold the relay baton, they hold it in the middle, believing that
  this will help them grip it best. This makes it hard for their teammate to grab the baton."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to hold the baton at the bottom when running, leaving more
  space for their teammate to hold when they changeover."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123401Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-successful-achieve-activities
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils might think they will only be successful if they can achieve all
  the activities at the most challenging level."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Everybody is different and success is different for everyone. Anyone who
  tries their best and gives maximum effort should feel successful, regardless of the level
  of challenge they completed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123430Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-active-fit-requires
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils might think that being active and fit requires gruelling, high
  impact activity, that maximises heart rate and leads to physical exhaustion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Activities should suit the goal you are trying to achieve. High impact,
  exhausting activities are suited to improve cardiovascular endurance. Low impact, relaxing
  exercising are suited to developing other components of fitness e.g. flexibility."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123436Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-hit-ball-hard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may try to hit the ball too hard when playing competitively. Pupils may
  be dishonest when scoring their own games in the competitions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise the importance of playing accurate and controlled shots rather than
  focusing on hitting the ball hard. Remind pupils of the importance of respect and playing
  by the rules in competitive situations, and to just focus on trying their best."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123447Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-celebration-shown-given-successful
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A celebration can only be shown or given when they have been successful."@en ;
  curric:correction """Children may feel a lack of inclusion and encouragement if acknowledgement of
  their efforts are only made when they have been successful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123453Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-batting-important-effective
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that batting is more important than effective fielding, when in
  fact, good fielding is equally vital to success in rounders."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand the importance of good tactics in both batting and
  fielding. Pupils should realise that if they limit their opponents from scoring rounders,
  it will be easier to win the game."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-batting-pair-pupils-poor-communicating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As a batting pair, pupils are often poor at communicating when to run,
  sometimes even oblivious of the need to communicate at all."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils a simple code that they can use and when to use it, to encourage
  more understanding of the need to communicate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123505Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-isnt-fair-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils feel it isn't fair when their opponents use a tactic against them; they
  fail to see the importance of taking time to consider how they can use their own power to
  gain an advantage."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Celebrate teams who deploy their powers at the right time as a result of
  careful planning. Consider awarding bonus points for this, even if the execution isn't
  successful. Award points to teams who focus on their own powers and not the opposition's."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124003Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-dodging-create-space
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might believe that by dodging they will always create space and outwit
  the defender. Pupils dodge to find a space then stand still waiting for a pass."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to remember that the defenders role is to respond to the dodge,
  therefore they may need to dodge again and look for new space. Persevering with this
  technique will help pupils successfully outwit their opponent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124014Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-spend-their-practice-time
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may spend their practice time adding more actions onto the
  sequence instead of repeating and refining a shorter sequence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Practice time can be used to repeat a skill and improve the quality of a
  performance, or it can be used to make changes to a sequence to improve the flow or
  increase the range of movements for more interest."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124073Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-teams-take-notice-ideas-shared
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Teams only take notice the ideas shared by the loudest team member."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils to encourage all teammates to share ideas, so that everyone
  feels included, especially those who may not contribute often and remain quiet in the
  backgound of everything."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124540Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-now-counter-tension-balances-counter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Now that counter tension balances and counter balances are used in the same
  lesson, pupils may mix them up."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise the difference between the two balances and that counter balances
  usually involve a pushing action and counter tension balances involve a pulling action."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124552Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-throw-shot-shot
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that you throw the shot in the shot put event, similar to how
  you throw the javelin."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Although 'throw' is often the terminology used when competing in the shot
  put, pupils should push the shot which starts from under their chin. A throwing action,
  when using a heavier shot, would likely cause a wrist/elblow/shoulder injury."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124563Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-close-together-demonstrates-frienship-kindness
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Being close together always demonstrates frienship, kindness and
  cooperation."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Being close suggests a cooperative connection between performers if the
  dynamic is smooth, calm and relaxed, however if the dynamic was strong, forceful and fast,
  the audience are likely to interpret their actions as demonstrating tension or anger."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124918Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-dont-discuss-benefits-potential
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils don't discuss the benefits or potential problems of each tactic or
  power before making a selection that is right for their team at the time. One pupil takes
  over and rushes the decision making."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that, for a tactic or power to have maximum impact and give their
  team a big advantage, they must discuss each option as a team."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124939Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-fielding-games-pupils-believe-retrieving
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When fielding in games, pupils believe that retrieving the ball and running it
  back to the bases is the most effective and quickest way to field."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to work as a team, by backing each other up and supporting
  each other. Ensure pupils understand that accurately throwing the ball to a teammate that
  is closer to the bases will be more effective and quicker than running with it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124958Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-fielding-pupils-retrieve-ball-run
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When fielding, pupils retrieve the ball and run with it in order to return it
  to the pupil on a base."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Tell the pupils that when fielding, they should work together as a team.
  Instead of running with the ball, they should quickly pass it to another player support,
  who needs to be close by and supporting. This will help move the ball faster."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124973Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-swimming-sidestroke-legs-perform-breaststroke
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When swimming sidestroke the legs perform a breaststroke action."@en ;
  curric:correction """From the starting position of one leg stacked on top of the other, the top
  leg moves forward and the bottom leg moves backwards, the legs then snap back together in
  the starting position."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124978Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-set-new-personal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that they will set a new personal best every time they attempt
  to and become disappointed if they don't."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that they need to show resilience to keep trying if
  they don't manage to set a personal best."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125893Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-shoot-score-forget
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils just want to shoot and score. They forget to look up and check to see
  if they should pass or dribble."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that we only shoot when we are in a suitable position and
  should take our time to make decisions first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-throw-ball-caught-stay
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will often throw the ball from where they have caught it, and then stay
  in that position. Pupils throw the ball towards their opponent instead of into space."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should be reminded to always return to the middle of the court after
  throwing the ball. Pupils should always be looking to throw ito space away from their
  opponent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125924Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-move-their-feet-striking
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils do not move their feet when striking the ball, leading to mistimed and
  awkward shots."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Almost every shot requires some foot movement and the players stance should
  allow for this by being on the balls of feet and with knees slightly bent. Practising
  footwork using a batting tee will make applying footwork to a moving ball easier."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126095Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-gaining-points-hit-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils are gaining points when they hit the ball into channels. This is only
  to practice creating space and pupils may think they score points in a game of tennis if
  they hit the ball into a channel."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is important to provide pupils with the context of why they are aiming for
  channels to try and create space within the rally so they attempt to aim for one channel
  and then the other to move their opponent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.128305Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-make-contact-shuttlecock
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to make contact with the shuttlecock when serving. Pupils
  may struggle to serve to the back of the court. Pupils may struggle to serve diagonally
  across the court or over the net."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could revert to serving by throwing the shuttlecock. Remind pupils to
  be side on with a wide stance to help generate more power. Make sure pupils feet are
  positioned correctly to serve diagonally. You can lower the net or use cones."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.128347Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-previously-learnt-rules
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget previously learnt rules and skills, leading them to chase after
  the ball instead of maintaining positions and structure."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that teamwork, communication, positioning and tactics can all
  lead to creating better chances, conceding less tries and scoring more tries."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.128489Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-rest-good-body-opposite-active
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Rest is not good for the body as it is the opposite of being active."@en ;
  curric:correction """Rest is really important to help the body recover, grow, repair and get
  stronger. However too much time not moving can cause the body to reduce fitness and
  strength."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.128518Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-challenged-adding-additional-actions-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When challenged with adding additional actions to their sequences as they
  finalise their work, pupils add in additional and unnecessary actions, coming away from
  the stipulated actions to include."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that extra actions don't necessarily improve the sequence and will
  make it very difficult for someone observing to evaulate their work."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.128549Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-fast-good-long
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that you have to be fast to be good at long distance running,
  overlooking the importance of endurance, breathing technique, pacing and tactics."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that sprinting and long-distance running differ: sprinters rely on
  fast-twitch muscle fibres for power and speed, while long-distance runners use slow-twitch
  fibres for endurance and efficiency."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.128556Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-selected-pupil-performing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that only the selected pupil performing in the event needs to
  focus on it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils understand that the whole team has a part to play in each
  event. Helping with tactics, motivating and encouraging each other are ways they can all
  be involved."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130212Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-way-make-certain-shape
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """There is only one way to make a certain shape (e.g. a wide star-shaped stretch
  for the letter 'X')."""@en ;
  curric:correction """There are many possible responses - the shapes can be recreated using just
  part of the body or all of it. Changing between sitting, lying and standing is also an
  option as well as incorporating balances or jumps."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130417Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-prepositions-used-writing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that prepositions are only used in writing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Prepositions describe how things are arranged relative to other people or
  objects, so they can be used in all subject areas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130423Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-partner-balance-counter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that a partner balance is a counter balance. Pupils may
  struggle with counter balance due to unequal weight distribution. Pupils may struggle to
  trust their partner."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show the difference between a partner balance and a counter balance. Pupils
  practice positions individually and work together to adjust the balance equally.
  Incorporate activities that require working together and communication to build trust."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130429Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-complete-their-sequence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may rush to complete their sequence and therefore do not perform to
  their potential. Pupils may give very brief, low quality feedback to their peers."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to reflect on feedback and keep striving to produce the best
  sequence by continually making changes to improve their performance. When pupils feedback
  to each other, encourage them to use key terminology and give quality feedback."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130446Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-strong-big-muscles
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Being strong is about having big muscles."@en ;
  curric:correction """Being physically strong relates to how our bodies are able to overcome the
  forces placed upon them. Strong muscles are essential for humans to complete everyday
  tasks and also help our joints to work effectively which helps to avoid injury and pain."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130452Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-effective-stretch-push
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils might think that for an effective stretch, you should push or
  reach until it is painful."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Stretching should never be painful. You might feel tension which can be
  described as resistance, a pull or tightening and this indicates that the muscle should
  not be stretched any further. Tension might ease with some deep breathing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130524Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-keep-their-head-water
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils keep their head away from the water."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should be made aware that if the face is in the water it is much
  easier for the legs to float."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130546Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-their-deep-breathing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils rush their deep breathing, which reduces the impact of the
  technique."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that it’s important not to rush deep breathing, otherwise
  they won’t be able to focus their minds and the technique won’t work."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.131658Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-grip-javelin-tightly-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils grip the javelin tightly in their hand, thinking that this will help
  them to throw it further, however this can hinder a smooth release and lead to tension in
  the rest of the arm."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should place the javelin across their palm with their fingers wrapped
  around it, but not too tight. Explain to pupils that a more relaxed grip will result in a
  smoother release and longer throw."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.131692Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-learning-swim-distances
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that learning to swim distances is more important than learning
  to rotate onto our backs."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Turning onto our back to float, and have the nose and mouth clear of the
  water, is an extremely important skill to learn as it means the airways are clear."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-equipment-use-activity
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that the more equipment they use in an activity, the better the
  activity will be."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand how to use equipment to enhance the activity. Too
  much equipment can make it confusing and unsafe."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132555Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-turn-without-checking-actually
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils turn without checking if there was actually space to turn into first.
  Pupils also turn when there is no need to."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils to check for the space before they turn. Explain that we turn
  when we need to change direction to move away from a defender."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-choose-movements-balances-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils choose movements and balances that only one pupil can perform as they
  are the actions they want to perform."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Support pupils to understand that they need to select movements and balances
  that both pupils in the pair can perform."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132740Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-interlocking-requires-us
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that interlocking requires us to connect together using our hands
  and arms."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Interlocking involves two or more things fitting together or overlapping,
  which could be done using a range of different body parts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-moving-canon-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that moving in canon means one person moves, then there is a
  pause before the next person moves, so the sequence becomes disjointed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that we need to ensure that one pupil is always moving or
  balancing to ensure the sequence flows."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133830Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-bounce-ball-hard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often try to bounce the ball too hard, resulting in dribbling it too
  high. Pupils believe they can only dribble with one hand."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Bending your knees and dribbling lower with control will make it harder for a
  defender to steal the ball. You can only dribble with one hand at a time, however
  switching between hands is an effective way to dribble with control."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133835Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-panic-defender-kick-strike
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils panic when there is a defender and kick/strike/throw the ball away
  quickly to prevent the defender getting too close to them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that if we panic, we will probably lose possession in a game.
  Encourage pupils to take their time. Bring in walking defenders instead to slow the game
  down."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133844Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-follow-other-teams-assuming
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils follow other teams assuming they’re going the correct way."@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight to pupils that orienteering is about independent navigation, and
  others can be wrong too."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133853Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-slow-end-race-sprint
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils slow down before the end of the race/ sprint, preparing to stop
  directly at the finish line."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that they should not begin to slow down until they have
  crossed the finish line as it will allow other runners to catch them up and potentially
  overtake them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134426Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-winning-everything-become
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that winning is everything and become disappointed if they fail
  to win every race."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to focus on personal improvement, teamwork and enjoying
  themselves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134433Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-suggest-jumping-mount-dismount
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may suggest jumping to mount and dismount apparatus as a change in
  level during their sequence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This lesson guide focuses on a change in level in relation to the surface of
  the apparatus i.e closer or further away. For example, from stomach, push into a plank.
  Jumping off changes levels in relation to the ground which is not the intended focus."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134444Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-oxygenated-blood-transported
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils might think that only oxygenated blood is transported around the
  body."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The body's cardiovascular system includes a group of organs and muscles that
  manage oxgenated blood and deoxygenated blood."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134450Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-throw-ball-much-power
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often throw the ball with too much power. Pupils step into their throw
  with the same foot as their throwing arm. Pupils wait for the ball to come to them instead
  of moving towards it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to hold the ball loosely rather than squeezing it tightly.
  Remind pupils to step in with opposite foot to throwing arm. Pupils should be encouraged
  to move towards the ball to catch it and make sure the body is underneath the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134760Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-floor-create-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils use the floor to create their linking movements in unison and move
  around the apparatus instead of using it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that the apparatus is there to be used and that we can
  really enhance our creativity if we try and include a range of apparatus in our movements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134765Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-moving-your-arms
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that moving your arms faster makes you swim faster."@en ;
  curric:correction """Catching and pulling the water slowly and effectively produces greater
  forward travel and increases speed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136891Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-lose-their-balance-fall
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When pupils lose their balance and fall forward into the water, they often
  instinctively try to place their hands onto the pool floor."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This significantly hinders pupils' ability to regain a standing position,
  often causing panic. Pupils should be taught how to regain a vertical position before, and
  at the start of, their first swimming lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hit-ball-flat-side
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils hit the ball with both the flat side and the curved side of their
  stick."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that they can only use the flat side of the stick and they lose
  possession if they break this rule."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136911Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-towards-player-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils rush in towards the player with the ball when defending. Often two
  pupils move towards the same attacker."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils need to stay on their toes ready to react and avoid diving in.
  Communication will prevent players from marking the same player and risk leaving other
  players open."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136917Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-contrast-means-opposite
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that contrast just means doing the opposite of someone else."@en ;
  curric:correction """Contrast in dance means that you are doing something distinctly different,
  for example, performing different directions, levels and pathways to each other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136925Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dance-count-music-8s
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "In dance, you count all music in 8's."@en ;
  curric:correction """In dance, counting corresponds to the musical time signature which varies
  enormously. Many are 4/4 timing and can be counted in patterns of 4's or 8's, others may
  be in contrasting patterns such as 3/4 or 6/8, so would need to be counted accordingly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137593Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-performing-flow-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may think that performing with flow means performing with
  speed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Sequences need control and smoothly linked movements. This creates a steady
  pace that feels fluid and not rushed. Balances create stillness and are held for a least 4
  seconds; flow can still be achieved even with still moments and steady movements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137605Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-change-overarm-throw-asking
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may change to an overarm throw when you are asking them to aim for the
  back of the court. Pupils may take too many risks when aiming for the perimeter and the
  ball goes out/hits the net a lot."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to step into their throw and follow throught towards their
  target to get more power behind their throw. Although we want pupils to aim away from the
  midle of the court, we still want them to successfully throw into the court area."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137611Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-hit-shuttlecock-back
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to hit the shuttlecock to the back of the court due to
  standing square on to the net. Pupils may avoid hitting backhand shots. Pupils may hit
  shuttlecock into the net."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils must work on a side on position when hitting the shuttlecock to
  generate more power. Pupils should work on their backhand technique to develop confidence.
  Remove or reduce the height of the net if pupils are struggling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137617Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hold-map-wrong-way
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils hold the map the wrong way round, not matching it to their direction of
  travel, making it harder to locate points accurately."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make sure pupils orient the map so it matches the direction they're facing.
  They must turn the map until the features on the map line up with what they can see around
  them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137622Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-hold-bat-attempt-strike
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils hold the bat and attempt to strike the ball using just 1 hand, like
  they would in similar sports, such as rounders."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that this approach can lead to a lack of control,
  making it difficult to play different shots. A correct 2 handed grip is essential for
  balance, precision and better shot execution."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137630Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-swim-back-paddle-leg
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils swim back paddle with a leg kick that is large, with the legs bending
  and the feet being low in the water."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The leg kick when swimming back paddle should be long and straight with small
  fast kicks which are near to or at the surface of the water."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137637Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-okay-turn-your
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that it is okay to turn over on to your front when finishing a
  backstroke race."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When swimming backstroke you should use the flags to count your strokes so
  that you finish a race on your back."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137654Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-strong-swimmers-dont-get-difficulty
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Strong swimmers don't get into difficulty in the water."@en ;
  curric:correction """Even strong swimmers can get into difficulty in the water if cold, tired,
  unwell or injured."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-take-strong-touches-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils take strong touches of the ball and move with the ball too far away
  from themselves so lose control easily."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils to take their time and keep the ball close to avoid losing
  control and possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-floor-piece-apparatus
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Some pupils may not recognise the floor as a piece of apparatus."@en ;
  curric:correction """The floor is a very demanding piece of apparatus because many different
  skills are required such as leaps, spins, splits, dance and acrobatics. In rhythmic
  gymnastics, additional apparatus is also used such as clubs, ribbons, hoops and balls."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138134Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-pupil-pulls-harder-doesnt
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """One pupil pulls harder or doesn’t pull enough, leading to an imbalance and
  collapse of the position. Pupils do not have a secure grip with one another"""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to communicate with their partners pulling gently at first,
  then increase force gradually to find the balance point. Encourage pupils to grip using
  wrists as an alternative to hands."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138149Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-counter-balances-involve-pushing-against
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Counter balances should always involve pushing against our partner's
  hands."""@en ;
  curric:correction """We often start by connecting using our hands. Once skilled at countering our
  partner, we can find different points of connection or use different levels or directions
  to make our combined shapes more interesting and creative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138160Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-travelling-around-room-means-run
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Travelling around the room means you run in a circle. Pausing and balancing
  are always star shapes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that travelling involves a wide range of actions including
  skipping, shuffling, marching, jumping, creeping. Also ensure pupils understand that we
  can balance on a range of body parts in a variety of shapes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138166Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-stand-still
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think they need to stand still and wait for the baton to be passed to
  them before they start running."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Encourage pupils start jogging as their teammate approaches them."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138171Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-swim-front-paddle-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils swim front paddle with their head out of the water."@en ;
  curric:correction "Get pupils to lean forwards to ensure their chin or face is in the water."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138897Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-move-close-ball-give
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will often move too close to the ball and not give themselves enough
  room to hit the ball accurately. Pupils will often hit the ball with too much power and a
  lack of control."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that the ball should be in front and slightly to the side of
  their body when they make contact with the ball. Pupils should be given time to experiment
  with the amount of power needed to hit the targets, and encourage a smooth swing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138902Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-use-physical-contact
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often believe they can use physical contact to tackle or push their
  opponent."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that tag rugby is a non-contact sport and pupils can only tag
  their opponents or intercept a pass."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138914Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-focus-winning-instead-adapting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils focus only on winning instead of adapting their tactics to the game
  scenario."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils have time to plan their tactics in each scenario and highlight
  effective team work."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138919Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-activities-fitness-solo
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils might think that activities for fitness are always solo tasks that
  don't encourage social interaction."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Being active with others can have lots of benefits, e.g. increased
  motivation, encouragement from others, and confidence. All these benefits combined, can
  encourage individuals to be more active, more often, resulting in increased activity
  levels."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-performing-animal-themed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that performing animal themed meditative balances requires acting
  like animals and making animal noises. This also means that pupils forget to control their
  breathing as they balance."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that if we make noises and actually act like animals, we
  are creating actions and using characterisation, not balancing to ensure calm, focus and
  relaxtion. We must remain silent and focus on long, slow breaths in and out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138934Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-holding-their-breath
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils sometimes think that holding their breath or shallow breathing helps
  them focus or exert more power."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils stay relaxed when sprinting and understand that deep rhythmic
  breaths will help their muscles recieve more oxygen to generate energy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138939Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-distinguish-matching-mirroring
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle to distinguish between a matching and mirroring movement.
  Pupils struggle to execute their movements simultaneously."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to work with peers to check whether a movement is matching
  or mirroring. Pupils should work on communication to improve their synchronisation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139438Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-their-shots-look
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will often rush their shots and look to try and score as soon as they
  get the ball, without considering their location in relation to the post or target."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils must remember that they have approximately 4 seconds to prepare and
  then shoot. Remind pupils that using the correct shooting technique will increase their
  chances of success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139444Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-embarrassed-admit-dont
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils feel embarrassed to admit when they don't understand a tactic or don't
  listen when tactics are being discussed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is really important to encourage pupils to be honest if they don't
  understand so that their teammates can explain to them. Celebrate and praise pupils/teams
  who ensure everyone understands, and individuals who speak up when they need help."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139450Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-defenders-believe-try-take-ball
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Defenders believe they can, or they try to, take the ball when they tag an
  opponent."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that the primary objective is to remove a tag from the ball
  carrier to stop their progress, rather than trying to take the ball."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139498Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-stop-movements-resulting-poor
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often stop between movements resulting in poor flow and continuity.
  This may be due to hesitancy or lack of confidence in their technique."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should repeat short sequences of movements until they are performed
  with flow. For example, focus on linking 2-3 movements together before adding more. Focus
  on flow before looking at speed routes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139509Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-throwing-underarm-pupils-struggle-release
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When throwing underarm, pupils often struggle to release the ball so it
  travels forward towards the target. Pupils may forget to have their hands up ready to
  catch the the ball."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to develop a smooth arm swing when throwing towards a target
  and finish with a straight arm pointing in the direction of their target. Remind pupils to
  adopt the ready position with hands up in front of them when waiting to catch."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140053Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-create-sequences-motifs-include
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils create sequences and motifs that include long stops between actions as
  pupils fail or forget to use additional actions to aid transition."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that in order to create a sequence that flows well, we need to
  include addtional actions to support the transition from action to action."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140086Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-applying-their-acceleration-skills-race
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When applying their acceleration skills to a race, pupils false start in an
  attempt to win."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that they need to start fast, reacting quickly to the start
  command, however, too many false starts can result in being disqualified."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140225Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-relate-negative-emotions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils struggle to relate to some of the negative emotions explored in the
  lesson and therefore don't see the benefit of practising the mime and meditative balance
  sequences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that it is important to practise and understand the
  benefits so that we are prepared for future challenges in our lives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140845Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-quality-performance-long
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils might think that a quality performance should be long and include
  difficult skills."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If a short sequence that includes easier skills is performed with accurate
  timings, fluidity, control and extension, this is demonstrating high quality. Evaluation
  should consider how something is performed as well as what is performed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140857Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-sprint-slow-sprint-again
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils sprint and then slow up and then sprint again and slow again,
  especially at the start of the run."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that having a steady rhythm may not get pupils to the front
  initially, but their overall time will be quicker than if they sprint and stop
  continuously."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140865Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-issues-group-dynamics-pupils-negotiate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """There may be issues with group dynamics as pupils have to negotiate which
  movements they will use when working in bigger groups. Not all pupils in the group may be
  able to perform the movements."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils may have to delegate a leader or be encouraged to listen to each other
  when working in bigger groups. Pupils may have to consider adapting their sequences when
  working with bigger groups."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141099Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-panic-receiving-ball-throw
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils panic when receiving the ball and throw it away quickly, especially if
  there is a defender close to them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that this may result in losing possession and that players have 4
  seconds before they have to pass. Encourage pupils to use this time to choose the most
  suitable pass."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-use-attacking-tactic
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils believe that when they use an attacking tactic it will always be
  successful."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that not all tactics work but they should continue to try hard
  and use a variety of tactics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141111Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-once-games-pupils-focus-much
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Once in games, pupils focus too much on just wanting to shoot and to win.
  Pupils forget the importance of their tactics and that they need to stay focused on the
  task ahead."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to focus on their tactics and to understand that it is the
  successful implementation of their tactics that will lead to success in the games."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141117Z"^^xsd:dateTime .
